"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkwebsite=globalThis.webpackChunkwebsite||[]).push([[1444],{3961(n){n.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"quan-ly-thoi-gian-cho-4-tuan-hoc-tap","metadata":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/quan-ly-thoi-gian-cho-4-tuan-hoc-tap","editUrl":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce/tree/main/website/blog/blog/2026-02-20-quan-ly-thoi-gian-cho-4-tuan-hoc-tap.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-20-quan-ly-thoi-gian-cho-4-tuan-hoc-tap.md","title":"Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian cho 4 tu\u1ea7n luy\u1ec7n thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9","description":"Luy\u1ec7n thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n l\xe0 m\u1ed9t th\u1eed th\xe1ch l\u1edbn. V\u1edbi c\xf4ng vi\u1ec7c, cu\u1ed9c s\u1ed1ng c\xe1 nh\xe2n v\xe0 h\xe0ng ng\xe0n concepts c\u1ea7n h\u1ecdc, qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian l\xe0 ch\xeca kh\xf3a th\xe0nh c\xf4ng. Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian \u0111\xe3 gi\xfap t\xf4i v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi.","date":"2026-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"quan-ly-thoi-gian","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/quan-ly-thoi-gian"},{"inline":true,"label":"meo-hoc","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/meo-hoc"},{"inline":true,"label":"study-tips","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/study-tips"},{"inline":true,"label":"productivity","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/productivity"},{"inline":true,"label":"bat-dau","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/bat-dau"}],"readingTime":7.81,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"H\u1ecdc L\u1ea1i","title":"Salesforce Platform Developer I Learner","url":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce","page":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/authors/hoclai"},"description":"Chia s\u1ebb h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 kinh nghi\u1ec7m v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497.png","key":"hoclai"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"quan-ly-thoi-gian-cho-4-tuan-hoc-tap","title":"Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian cho 4 tu\u1ea7n luy\u1ec7n thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9","authors":["hoclai"],"tags":["quan-ly-thoi-gian","meo-hoc","study-tips","productivity","bat-dau"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i tr\u01b0\u1edbc k\u1ef3 thi: Chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c \xf4n t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi"}},"content":"Luy\u1ec7n thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 **Salesforce Platform Developer I** trong 4 tu\u1ea7n l\xe0 m\u1ed9t th\u1eed th\xe1ch l\u1edbn. V\u1edbi c\xf4ng vi\u1ec7c, cu\u1ed9c s\u1ed1ng c\xe1 nh\xe2n v\xe0 h\xe0ng ng\xe0n concepts c\u1ea7n h\u1ecdc, qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian l\xe0 ch\xeca kh\xf3a th\xe0nh c\xf4ng. Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian \u0111\xe3 gi\xfap t\xf4i v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Th\xe1ch th\u1ee9c c\u1ee7a 4-week intensive learning\\n\\nH\u1ecdc t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao trong 4 tu\u1ea7n mang l\u1ea1i nh\u1eefng th\xe1ch th\u1ee9c:\\n\\n```\\nChallenges:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Th\u1eddi gian h\u1ea1n ch\u1ebf (7 ng\xe0y \xd7 4 tu\u1ea7n = 28 ng\xe0y)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Kh\u1ed1i l\u01b0\u1ee3ng ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c l\u1edbn (Admin, Apex, LWC, Integration)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 C\u1ea7n balance v\u1edbi work/life\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 R\u1ee7i ro burnout\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Pressure t\u1eeb deadline (exam date)\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc5 K\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp 4 tu\u1ea7n chi ti\u1ebft\\n\\n### T\u1ed5ng quan th\u1eddi gian\\n\\n```\\nWeekly Time Allocation (Total: ~50 hours/week):\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 1: Admin & Flow\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Morning (8:00-12:00): 20 gi\u1edd - Trailhead & Docs\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Afternoon (13:00-18:00): 25 gi\u1edd - Hands-on practice\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Evening (20:00-22:00): 10 gi\u1edd - Review & Prep\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Weekend: 5 gi\u1edd - Extra practice\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 2: Apex & SOQL\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Morning: 20 gi\u1edd - Apex syntax & concepts\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Afternoon: 25 gi\u1edd - Coding & Triggers\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Evening: 10 gi\u1edd - Practice questions\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Weekend: 5 gi\u1edd - Debugging & Refactoring\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 3: LWC\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Morning: 20 gi\u1edd - LWC concepts & LDS\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Afternoon: 25 gi\u1edd - Component development\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Evening: 10 gi\u1edd - Testing & Integration\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Weekend: 5 gi\u1edd - Chart.js integration\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 4: Exam Prep\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Morning: 20 gi\u1edd - Review topics\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Afternoon: 25 gi\u1edd - Practice questions\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Evening: 10 gi\u1edd - Mock exams\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Weekend: 5 gi\u1edd - Final prep\\n```\\n\\n### K\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch h\xe0ng ng\xe0y (Daily Schedule)\\n\\n```\\nDaily Learning Schedule:\\n\\nMorning Session (8:00-12:00) - 4 hours\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 08:00-08:30 | Review yesterday    \u2502\\n\u2502 08:30-10:00 | Learn new topics    \u2502\\n\u2502 10:00-10:15 | Break               \u2502\\n\u2502 10:15-12:00 | Continue learning   \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n\\nLunch Break (12:00-13:00)\\n\\nAfternoon Session (13:00-18:00) - 5 hours\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 13:00-14:30 | Hands-on practice   \u2502\\n\u2502 14:30-14:45 | Break               \u2502\\n\u2502 14:45-16:30 | Continue practice   \u2502\\n\u2502 16:30-16:45 | Break               \u2502\\n\u2502 16:45-18:00 | Build projects     \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n\\nDinner Break (18:00-20:00)\\n\\nEvening Session (20:00-22:00) - 2 hours\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 20:00-20:30 | Review notes        \u2502\\n\u2502 20:30-21:30 | Practice questions  \u2502\\n\u2502 21:30-22:00 | Prep for tomorrow  \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n```\\n\\n## \u26a1 K\u1ef9 thu\u1eadt qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian hi\u1ec7u qu\u1ea3\\n\\n### 1. Pomodoro Technique\\n\\nS\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Pomodoro \u0111\u1ec3 maintain focus:\\n\\n```\\nWork-Work-Focus-Focus Pattern:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 25 minutes focused work\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 5 minutes short break\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 25 minutes focused work\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 5 minutes short break\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 25 minutes focused work\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 5 minutes short break\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 25 minutes focused work\\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 15-30 minutes long break\\n\\nTotal: ~2 hours work\\n```\\n\\n**L\u1ee3i \xedch:**\\n- Gi\u1eef focus cao\\n- Tr\xe1nh mental fatigue\\n- T\u0103ng productivity\\n- D\u1ec5 tracking progress\\n\\n### 2. Time Blocking\\n\\nChia th\u1eddi gian th\xe0nh blocks cho c\xe1c tasks kh\xe1c nhau:\\n\\n```yaml\\nMorning Blocks (Learning):\\n  - 8:00-9:30: New concepts (Deep work)\\n  - 9:45-11:15: Documentation reading\\n  - 11:30-12:00: Quick summary\\n\\nAfternoon Blocks (Practice):\\n  - 13:00-14:30: Coding exercises\\n  - 14:45-16:15: Build projects\\n  - 16:30-18:00: Debug & fix issues\\n\\nEvening Blocks (Review):\\n  - 20:00-20:30: Daily review\\n  - 20:30-21:30: Practice questions\\n  - 21:30-22:00: Tomorrow prep\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Eat the Frog\\n\\nL\xe0m task kh\xf3 nh\u1ea5t v\xe0o bu\u1ed5i s\xe1ng:\\n\\n```\\nDaily Priority Order:\\n1. \\"Eat the Frog\\": Task kh\xf3 nh\u1ea5t/v quan tr\u1ecdng nh\u1ea5t\\n2. High priority: Tasks c\u1ea7n ho\xe0n th\xe0nh h\xf4m nay\\n3. Medium priority: Tasks n\xean ho\xe0n th\xe0nh\\n4. Low priority: Tasks c\xf3 th\u1ec3 postpone\\n```\\n\\n**V\xed d\u1ee5:**\\n- Bu\u1ed5i s\xe1ng: H\u1ecdc Apex Triggers (kh\xf3 nh\u1ea5t)\\n- Bu\u1ed5i chi\u1ec1u: Practice coding (medium)\\n- Bu\u1ed5i t\u1ed1i: Review notes (easy)\\n\\n### 4. Two-Minute Rule\\n\\nN\u1ebfu task m\u1ea5t < 2 ph\xfat, l\xe0m ngay:\\n\\n```\\nExamples:\\n\u2705 Reply email: Do now\\n\u2705 Note down idea: Do now\\n\u2705 Save code snippet: Do now\\n\u274c Debug complex issue: Schedule for later\\n\u274c Build new component: Schedule for later\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f C\xf4ng c\u1ee5 v\xe0 Apps t\xf4i s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng\\n\\n### Productivity Apps\\n\\n```\\nTime Tracking:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Toggl: Track time spent on tasks\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 RescueTime: Monitor productivity\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Toggl Track: Daily/weekly reports\\n\\nTask Management:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Notion: Project tracking & notes\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Trello: Kanban board for tasks\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Todoist: Daily to-do lists\\n\\nFocus & Concentration:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Forest: Gamify focus time\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Brain.fm: Focus music\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Freedom: Block distractions\\n\\nLearning Tools:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Anki: Flashcards for memorization\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Obsidian: Knowledge management\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Notion: Course notes\\n```\\n\\n### K\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch theo d\xf5i (Tracking Template)\\n\\n**Weekly Tracker in Notion:**\\n\\n```markdown\\n# Week 1: Admin & Flow\\n\\n## Goals\\n- [ ] Complete 15 Trailhead badges\\n- [ ] Build Project Management App\\n- [ ] Create 5 Flow automations\\n- [ ] Score 70%+ on practice questions\\n\\n## Daily Progress\\n\\n### Day 1\\n- Morning: \u2705 Completed Trailhead Admin Beginner\\n- Afternoon: \u2705 Created Project__c object\\n- Evening: \u2705 Learned Flow basics\\n- Notes: Flow is powerful! Need more practice\\n\\n### Day 2\\n- Morning: \u2705 Completed Security module\\n- Afternoon: \u26a0\ufe0f Struggled with sharing rules\\n- Evening: \u2705 Fixed sharing issues\\n- Notes: Need to review role hierarchy\\n\\n## Time Allocation\\n- Total study time: 50 hours\\n- Trailhead: 20 hours (40%)\\n- Practice: 25 hours (50%)\\n- Review: 5 hours (10%)\\n\\n## Next Week Prep\\n- Install Salesforce CLI\\n- Read Apex documentation\\n- Practice Java basics\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83e\udde0 K\u1ef9 thu\u1eadt h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp hi\u1ec7u qu\u1ea3\\n\\n### 1. Active Learning\\n\\nThay v\xec ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u1ecdc, h\xe3y th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh:\\n\\n```\\n\u274c Passive Learning:\\n- Read documentation\\n- Watch videos\\n- Listen to podcasts\\n\\n\u2705 Active Learning:\\n- Build projects\\n- Write code\\n- Teach others\\n- Practice questions\\n- Create cheat sheets\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Spaced Repetition\\n\\nReview ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c theo intervals:\\n\\n```\\nSpaced Repetition Schedule:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 1: Learn new concept\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 2: Review (1 day later)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 4: Review (2 days later)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 7: Review (3 days later)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 14: Review (1 week later)\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Day 30: Review (2 weeks later)\\n```\\n\\n**Tools:**\\n- Anki: Flashcards v\u1edbi spaced repetition\\n- Quizlet: Study sets\\n- RemNote: Notes + spaced repetition\\n\\n### 3. Feynman Technique\\n\\nH\xe3y gi\u1ea3ng l\u1ea1i nh\u1eefng g\xec b\u1ea1n h\u1ecdc:\\n\\n```\\nFeynman Technique Steps:\\n1. Choose a concept\\n2. Teach it to someone (or yourself)\\n3. Identify gaps in understanding\\n4. Review and simplify\\n\\nExample:\\nTeach Apex Triggers to:\\n- Colleague\\n- Friend\\n- Or even just explain to yourself\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Interleaving\\n\\nMix c\xe1c topics thay v\xec h\u1ecdc t\u1eebng topic m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch tu\u1ea7n t\u1ef1:\\n\\n```\\n\u274c Block Learning:\\nDay 1-7: Only Admin\\nDay 8-14: Only Apex\\nDay 15-21: Only LWC\\n\\n\u2705 Interleaved Learning:\\nDay 1: Admin + Flow\\nDay 2: Apex + Admin\\nDay 3: LWC + Apex\\nDay 4: Flow + LWC\\n```\\n\\n**L\u1ee3i \xedch:**\\n- Better retention\\n- Improved problem-solving\\n- Better transfer of knowledge\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcaa Tr\xe1nh Burnout\\n\\n### Signs of Burnout\\n\\n```\\nWarning Signs:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Mental fatigue/exhaustion\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Lack of motivation\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Difficulty concentrating\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Sleep problems\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Physical symptoms (headache, etc.)\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Irritability/anxiety\\n```\\n\\n### Prevention Strategies\\n\\n```yaml\\nDaily Self-Care:\\n  morning:\\n    - 7-8 hours sleep\\n    - Healthy breakfast\\n    - Light exercise/stretching\\n  during study:\\n    - Take regular breaks (every 25-30 min)\\n    - Stay hydrated\\n    - Get fresh air\\n  evening:\\n    - Wind down routine\\n    - No screens 1 hour before bed\\n    - Relaxation (meditation, reading)\\n\\nWeekly Self-Care:\\n  - 1 rest day per week\\n  - Social activities\\n  - Physical exercise (3-4x/week)\\n  - Hobbies unrelated to tech\\n\\nMonthly Self-Care:\\n  - Massage/sauna\\n  - Weekend getaway\\n  - Social events\\n  - Reflection & goal review\\n```\\n\\n### Energy Management\\n\\n```\\nEnergy Levels Throughout Day:\\n\\nHigh Energy (8:00-11:00):\\n  - Deep work: New concepts, complex topics\\n  - Coding challenges\\n  - Problem-solving\\n\\nMedium Energy (13:00-16:00):\\n  - Practice exercises\\n  - Build projects\\n  - Documentation reading\\n\\nLow Energy (20:00-22:00):\\n  - Review notes\\n  - Practice questions\\n  - Prepare for tomorrow\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca Tracking Progress\\n\\n### Weekly Metrics\\n\\n```\\nWeek 1 Metrics:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Study hours: 50\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Trailhead badges: 15\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Practice questions: 100\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Projects completed: 1\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Confidence level: 6/10\\n\\nWeek 2 Metrics:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Study hours: 52\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Apex classes created: 8\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Practice questions: 150\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Triggers built: 3\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Confidence level: 7/10\\n\\nWeek 3 Metrics:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Study hours: 48\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 LWC components: 6\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Practice questions: 120\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Test coverage: 80%+\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Confidence level: 8/10\\n\\nWeek 4 Metrics:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Study hours: 55\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Practice questions: 300\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Mock exams: 3\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Final exam score: 85%\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Confidence level: 9/10\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Tips cho Success\\n\\n### Before Starting\\n\\n1. **Set clear goals**: Bi\u1ebft ch\xednh x\xe1c b\u1ea1n mu\u1ed1n \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c\\n2. **Create a schedule**: Plan tr\u01b0\u1edbc, don\'t wing it\\n3. **Set up environment**: Quiet, comfortable workspace\\n4. **Gather resources**: All materials ready beforehand\\n5. **Tell friends/family**: Get support and understanding\\n\\n### During Learning\\n\\n1. **Follow the schedule**: Stick to your plan\\n2. **Take breaks regularly**: Don\'t burnout\\n3. **Stay hydrated**: Drink water throughout the day\\n4. **Eat healthy**: Fuel your brain properly\\n5. **Stay organized**: Keep notes and materials organized\\n\\n### When Stuck\\n\\n1. **Don\'t panic**: It\'s normal to get stuck\\n2. **Take a break**: Fresh eyes help\\n3. **Ask for help**: Use Stack Exchange, forums\\n4. **Move on temporarily**: Come back later\\n5. **Break it down**: Smaller problems are easier\\n\\n### Before Exam\\n\\n1. **Get enough sleep**: 8+ hours night before\\n2. **Review cheat sheets**: Quick refresher\\n3. **Stay calm**: You\'ve prepared well\\n4. **Believe in yourself**: You can do this!\\n5. **Celebrate after**: Reward your hard work\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3\\n\\nV\u1edbi chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian n\xe0y, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3:\\n\\n- \u2705 **Study 200+ hours** trong 4 tu\u1ea7n\\n- \u2705 **Complete all goals** cho t\u1eebng tu\u1ea7n\\n- \u2705 **Pass exam** v\u1edbi 85% score\\n- \u2705 **Maintain work-life balance**\\n- \u2705 **Avoid burnout**\\n- \u2705 **Enjoy the process**\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcad Nh\u1eefng b\xe0i h\u1ecdc quan tr\u1ecdng\\n\\n1. **Planning is everything**: Good plan = better results\\n2. **Consistency beats intensity**: Study daily, not binge\\n3. **Quality over quantity**: Focus on understanding, not hours\\n4. **Take care of yourself**: Health enables learning\\n5. **Stay flexible**: Adjust plan when needed\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcdd L\u1eddi khuy\xean cho b\u1ea1n\\n\\nN\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n \u0111ang chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho 4-week intensive learning:\\n\\n1. **Start with a plan**: Don\'t just start, plan first\\n2. **Use productivity tools**: They help you stay on track\\n3. **Take breaks seriously**: Rest is part of learning\\n4. **Track your progress**: See how far you\'ve come\\n5. **Stay healthy**: Physical health = mental performance\\n6. **Be flexible**: Adjust when life happens\\n7. **Believe in yourself**: You can do it!\\n\\n---\\n\\n**B\u1ea1n c\xf3 c\xe2u h\u1ecfi g\xec v\u1ec1 qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian? H\xe3y \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea1i b\xecnh lu\u1eadn b\xean d\u01b0\u1edbi!** \ud83d\udcac\\n\\n**Tags**: #Salesforce #PlatformDeveloperI #TimeManagement #StudyTips #Productivity #Learning"},{"id":"tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi","metadata":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi","editUrl":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce/tree/main/website/blog/blog/2026-02-15-tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-15-tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi.md","title":"Tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i tr\u01b0\u1edbc k\u1ef3 thi: Chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c \xf4n t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao","description":"\u0110\xe2y l\xe0 n\xf3! Tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng tr\u01b0\u1edbc k\u1ef3 thi Salesforce Platform Developer I. Sau 3 tu\u1ea7n h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp, \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 l\xfac \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1eadp trung ho\xe0n to\xe0n v\xe0o \xf4n t\u1eadp v\xe0 chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho k\u1ef3 thi th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf. Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c \xf4n t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao c\u1ee7a m\xecnh.","date":"2026-02-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"tuan-4","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/tuan-4"},{"inline":true,"label":"luyen-thi","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/luyen-thi"},{"inline":true,"label":"exam-prep","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/exam-prep"},{"inline":true,"label":"governor-limits","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/governor-limits"},{"inline":true,"label":"strategy","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/strategy"}],"readingTime":7.76,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"H\u1ecdc L\u1ea1i","title":"Salesforce Platform Developer I Learner","url":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce","page":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/authors/hoclai"},"description":"Chia s\u1ebb h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 kinh nghi\u1ec7m v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497.png","key":"hoclai"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi","title":"Tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i tr\u01b0\u1edbc k\u1ef3 thi: Chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c \xf4n t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao","authors":["hoclai"],"tags":["tuan-4","luyen-thi","exam-prep","governor-limits","strategy"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian cho 4 tu\u1ea7n luy\u1ec7n thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/quan-ly-thoi-gian-cho-4-tuan-hoc-tap"},"nextItem":{"title":"B\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u v\u1edbi LWC: Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c trong Tu\u1ea7n 3","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/bat-dau-voi-lwc"}},"content":"\u0110\xe2y l\xe0 n\xf3! Tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng tr\u01b0\u1edbc k\u1ef3 thi **Salesforce Platform Developer I**. Sau 3 tu\u1ea7n h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp, \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 l\xfac \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1eadp trung ho\xe0n to\xe0n v\xe0o \xf4n t\u1eadp v\xe0 chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho k\u1ef3 thi th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf. Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c \xf4n t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao c\u1ee7a m\xecnh.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf T\u1ed5ng quan Tu\u1ea7n 4\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 4 l\xe0 giai \u0111o\u1ea1n **intensive review** v\xe0 **exam preparation**:\\n\\n```\\nTu\u1ea7n 4 Schedule:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Days 1-2: Review to\xe0n b\u1ed9 ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Days 3-4: Practice questions (Focus on Force)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 5: Mock exams & Weakness analysis\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Day 6: Final review & Cheat sheet creation\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Day 7: EXAM DAY! \ud83c\udf89\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb K\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch chi ti\u1ebft theo ng\xe0y\\n\\n### Day 1-2: Comprehensive Review\\n\\n**M\u1ee5c ti\xeau**: Review to\xe0n b\u1ed9 ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c t\u1eeb 3 tu\u1ea7n tr\u01b0\u1edbc\\n\\n**B\u1ea3ng theo d\xf5i:**\\n\\n| Ch\u1ee7 \u0111\u1ec1 | Tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i | Th\u1eddi gian | Notes |\\n|--------|-----------|-----------|-------|\\n| Admin & Configuration | \u2705 | 3 gi\u1edd | Mastered |\\n| Security & Access | \u2705 | 3 gi\u1edd | Good understanding |\\n| Data Modeling | \u2705 | 2 gi\u1edd | Clear |\\n| Business Logic | \u2705 | 4 gi\u1edd | Need more practice |\\n| User Interface | \u2705 | 3 gi\u1edd | Good |\\n| App Deployment | \u2705 | 2 gi\u1edd | OK |\\n\\n**C\xe1ch t\xf4i review:**\\n\\n1. **Xem l\u1ea1i t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 notes**: \u0110\u1ecdc qua c\xe1c notes t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 vi\u1ebft\\n2. **Refresher labs**: L\xe0m l\u1ea1i c\xe1c labs quan tr\u1ecdng\\n3. **Watch review videos**: Xem l\u1ea1i c\xe1c video tutorial\\n4. **Create summary documents**: T\u1ea1o t\xf3m t\u1eaft cho t\u1eebng topic\\n\\n### Day 3-4: Practice Questions (Focus on Force)\\n\\n**M\u1ee5c ti\xeau**: L\xe0m 300+ c\xe2u h\u1ecfi practice\\n\\n**K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3:**\\n\\n```\\nFocus on Force Questions:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Total Questions: 350\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Correct: 275 (78.6%)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Incorrect: 75 (21.4%)\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Topics c\u1ea7n improve:\\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 Governor Limits (15 questions)\\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 Asynchronous Apex (12 questions)\\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 Security & Sharing (10 questions)\\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Integration patterns (8 questions)\\n```\\n\\n**Chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c l\xe0m questions:**\\n\\n1. **L\xe0m theo topic**: \u0110\u1eebng l\xe0m random, focus t\u1eebng topic\\n2. **Hi\u1ec3u t\u1ea1i sai sai**: \u0110\u1eebng ch\u1ec9 nh\u1edb \u0111\xe1p \xe1n \u0111\xfang\\n3. **Review immediately**: Sau khi l\xe0m m\u1ed7i set 20-30 questions, review ngay\\n4. **Mark difficult questions**: \u0110\xe1nh d\u1ea5u \u0111\u1ec3 review l\u1ea1i sau\\n\\n**V\xed d\u1ee5 ph\xe2n t\xedch c\xe2u h\u1ecfi sai:**\\n\\n```\\nC\xe2u h\u1ecfi: Governor Limits - SOQL Queries\\n\\nC\xe2u c\u1ee7a t\xf4i: 100 SOQL queries per transaction\\n\u0110\xe1p \xe1n \u0111\xfang: 100 SOQL queries per transaction\\n\\nT\xf4i ngh\u0129: \u0110\xfang r\u1ed3i m\xe0?\\nReal answer: \u0110\xfang, nh\u01b0ng c\xf3 nuance - 100 t\u1ed5ng, kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i 100 trong loop\\n\\nB\xe0i h\u1ecdc: C\u1ea9n th\u1eadn v\u1edbi bulk operations v\xe0 transactions\\n```\\n\\n### Day 5: Mock Exams & Weakness Analysis\\n\\n**M\u1ee5c ti\xeau**: L\xe0m 3 mock exams \u0111\u1ec3 ki\u1ec3m tra th\u1ef1c l\u1ef1c\\n\\n**K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 Mock Exams:**\\n\\n```\\nMock Exam 1: 68/100 (68%)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Strong areas: Admin (85%), Data Modeling (80%)\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Weak areas: Asynchronous Apex (55%), Limits (60%)\\n\\nMock Exam 2: 72/100 (72%)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Improved: Asynchronous Apex (65%)\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Still weak: Integration patterns (58%)\\n\\nMock Exam 3: 78/100 (78%)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Final score: Passing! \u2705\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Confidence: High\\n```\\n\\n**Chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c sau mock exams:**\\n\\n1. **Analyze patterns**: Xem x\xe9t types of questions t\xf4i th\u01b0\u1eddng sai\\n2. **Focus on weak areas**: D\xe0nh nhi\u1ec1u th\u1eddi gian h\u01a1n cho c\xe1c ch\u1ee7 \u0111\u1ec1 y\u1ebfu\\n3. **Time management**: Luy\u1ec7n t\u1eadp \u0111\u1ec3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh trong 105 ph\xfat\\n4. **Review explanations**: \u0110\u1ecdc k\u1ef9 gi\u1ea3i th\xedch cho m\u1ed7i c\xe2u h\u1ecfi\\n\\n### Day 6: Final Review & Cheat Sheet Creation\\n\\n**M\u1ee5c ti\xeau**: T\u1ea1o cheat sheet v\xe0 final review\\n\\n**Cheat Sheet t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o:**\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc4 Governor Limits Cheat Sheet\\n\\n```yaml\\nSOQL Queries:\\n  - Synchronous: 100\\n  - Asynchronous: 200\\n  - Per transaction: 100\\n\\nDML Statements:\\n  - Synchronous: 150\\n  - Asynchronous: 150\\n  - Per transaction: 150\\n\\nHeap Size:\\n  - Sync: 6 MB\\n  - Async: 12 MB\\n  - Per transaction: 6 MB/12 MB\\n\\nCallouts:\\n  - Per transaction: 100\\n  - Timeout: 120 seconds\\n\\nCPU Time:\\n  - Sync: 10,000 ms (10 seconds)\\n  - Async: 60,000 ms (60 seconds)\\n\\nRecords Retrieved:\\n  - SOQL: 50,000\\n  - SOSL: 2,000\\n\\nEmails:\\n  - SingleEmailMessage: 5,000 per day\\n  - MassEmailMessage: 5,000 per day\\n  - Daily limit: 5,000 total\\n\\nBatch Apex:\\n  - Batch size: 1-200 records\\n  - Batches per transaction: 5\\n\\nFuture Methods:\\n  - Queueable: 50 per transaction\\n  - Future: 50 per transaction\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc4 Security Cheat Sheet\\n\\n```\\nObject-Level Security:\\n  - Profiles: Base permissions\\n  - Permission Sets: Additional permissions\\n  - CRUD: Create, Read, Update, Delete\\n\\nField-Level Security:\\n  - Profiles: Set accessibility\\n  - Permission Sets: Add accessibility\\n\\nRecord-Level Security:\\n  - Org-wide defaults: Baseline access\\n  - Role Hierarchy: Automatic sharing\\n  - Sharing Rules: Manual exceptions\\n  - Manual Sharing: Owner/Manager sharing\\n\\nSharing Keywords (Apex):\\n  - with sharing: Enforce sharing rules\\n  - without sharing: Ignore sharing rules\\n  - inherited sharing: Use current context\\n\\nApex Security:\\n  - CRUD/FLS checks: Use Schema methods\\n  - SO injection prevention: Use bind variables\\n  - XSS prevention: Use HTMLEncode/CJSEncode\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc4 Asynchronous Apex Cheat Sheet\\n\\n```\\nFuture Methods:\\n  @future static void methodName() {\\n    // Must be static\\n    // Cannot return value\\n    // Cannot accept objects as parameters\\n  }\\n\\nQueueable Interface:\\n  public class MyQueueable implements Queueable {\\n    public void execute(QueueableContext context) {\\n      // Can accept objects\\n      // Can chain queueable jobs\\n      // Monitor in Apex Jobs\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\nBatch Apex:\\n  public class MyBatch implements Database.Batchable {\\n    public start(BatchableContext) {\\n      // Define scope\\n    }\\n    \\n    public execute(BatchableContext, List<SObject>) {\\n      // Process records in chunks\\n    }\\n    \\n    public finish(BatchableContext) {\\n      // Cleanup/notifications\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\nScheduled Apex:\\n  public class ScheduledBatch implements Schedulable {\\n    public void execute(SchedulableContext) {\\n      // Schedule batch jobs\\n    }\\n  }\\n```\\n\\n### Day 7: EXAM DAY! \ud83c\udf89\\n\\n**Chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho exam:**\\n\\n1. **Sleep well**: 8+ ti\u1ebfng ng\u1ee7 \u0111\xeam tr\u01b0\u1edbc\\n2. **Eat healthy**: B\u1eefa s\xe1ng \u0111\u1ea7y \u0111\u1ee7 dinh d\u01b0\u1ee1ng\\n3. **Arrive early**: \u0110\u1ebfn s\u1edbm 30 ph\xfat\\n4. **Bring ID**: Gi\u1ea5y t\u1edd t\xf9y th\xe2n\\n5. **Water & snacks**: N\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0 \u0111\u1ed3 \u0103n nh\u1eb9\\n\\n**Trong exam:**\\n\\n```\\nStrategy:\\n1. Review all questions first (5 minutes)\\n2. Mark difficult questions (skip for now)\\n3. Answer easy questions first\\n4. Return to marked questions\\n5. Review all answers (10 minutes)\\n6. Submit! \ud83d\ude80\\n\\nTime Management:\\n- Total time: 105 minutes\\n- Questions: 60\\n- Average per question: ~1.75 minutes\\n- Review time: 15 minutes\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca Exam Results\\n\\n```\\nFinal Score: 85/100 (85%) \u2705 PASS!\\n\\nBreakdown by Section:\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Configuration & Setup: 90%\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Object Manager & Lightning App Builder: 85%\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Sales & Marketing Applications: 80%\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Service & Support Applications: 75%\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Productivity & Collaboration: 85%\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Data & Analytics Management: 80%\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Security & Access: 85%\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 App Deployment: 90%\\n\\nAreas of Strength:\\n  \u2705 Governor Limits\\n  \u2705 Security model\\n  \u2705 Asynchronous Apex\\n  \u2705 LWC basics\\n\\nAreas to Improve:\\n  \u26a0\ufe0f Integration patterns\\n  \u26a0\ufe0f Advanced LWC concepts\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udca1 Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i l\xe0m \u0111\xfang\\n\\n### 1. Start early v\u1edbi practice questions\\n\\n```\\n\u274c Kh\xf4ng n\xean: \u0110\u1ee3i \u0111\u1ebfn tu\u1ea7n 4 m\u1edbi l\xe0m questions\\n\u2705 N\xean: B\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u l\xe0m questions t\u1eeb tu\u1ea7n 1-2\\n```\\n\\nT\xf4i b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u l\xe0m practice questions t\u1eeb tu\u1ea7n 2, gi\xfap t\xf4i:\\n- Nh\u1eadn ra c\xe1c patterns trong exam questions\\n- Hi\u1ec3u s\xe2u h\u01a1n v\u1ec1 c\xe1c topics\\n- C\xf3 th\u1eddi gian review v\xe0 improve\\n\\n### 2. Focus on weak areas\\n\\nSau m\u1ed7i mock exam, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3:\\n- Ph\xe2n t\xedch k\u1ef9 areas t\xf4i sai\\n- D\xe0nh extra time \u0111\u1ec3 h\u1ecdc l\u1ea1i\\n- L\xe0m th\xeam practice questions cho c\xe1c topics \u0111\xf3\\n\\n### 3. Create cheat sheets\\n\\nCheat sheets gi\xfap t\xf4i:\\n- Quick review tr\u01b0\u1edbc exam\\n- Visualize relationships gi\u1eefa concepts\\n- C\xf3 reference document cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng\\n\\n### 4. Practice time management\\n\\nT\xf4i \u0111\xe3 luy\u1ec7n t\u1eadp:\\n- Ho\xe0n th\xe0nh mock exams trong 105 ph\xfat\\n- Kh\xf4ng b\u1ecb stuck tr\xean difficult questions\\n- C\xf3 th\u1eddi gian \u0111\u1ec3 review answers\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i n\xean l\xe0m t\u1ed1t h\u01a1n\\n\\n### 1. Review integration patterns s\u1edbm h\u01a1n\\n\\nT\xf4i \u0111\xe3 review integration patterns qu\xe1 mu\u1ed9n. N\xean:\\n- \u0110\u1ecdc documentation s\u1edbm h\u01a1n\\n- L\xe0m practice questions cho integration t\u1eeb tu\u1ea7n 2\\n- Hi\u1ec3u c\xe1c use cases c\u1ee7a t\u1eebng pattern\\n\\n### 2. L\u01b0u notes cho tricky questions\\n\\nC\xf3 nh\u1eefng questions r\u1ea5t tricky m\xe0 t\xf4i g\u1eb7p nhi\u1ec1u l\u1ea7n. N\xean:\\n- Note down nh\u1eefng questions \u0111\xf3\\n- Hi\u1ec3u t\u1ea1i sao n\xf3 tricky\\n- T\u1ea1o strategy \u0111\u1ec3 handle nh\u1eefng types of questions \u0111\xf3\\n\\n### 3. Practice more on real scenarios\\n\\nT\xf4i \u0111\xe3 h\u1ecdc qu\xe1 nhi\u1ec1u theory. N\xean:\\n- T\u1ea1o c\xe1c real-world scenarios\\n- Practice tr\xean Developer Org\\n- Build complex features\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Tips cho Exam Day\\n\\n### Before Exam\\n\\n1. **Know the rules**: Hi\u1ec3u r\xf5 exam policies\\n2. **Check your equipment**: \u0110\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o computer/network stable\\n3. **Bring necessary items**: ID, water, snacks\\n4. **Mental preparation**: Th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh breathing exercises\\n\\n### During Exam\\n\\n1. **Read questions carefully**: \u0110\u1eebng v\u1ed9i\\n2. **Eliminate obviously wrong answers**: Narrow down options\\n3. **Watch for keywords**: \\"BEST\\", \\"NOT\\", \\"EXCEPT\\"\\n4. **Manage time**: \u0110\u1eebng spend qu\xe1 nhi\u1ec1u time tr\xean m\u1ed9t c\xe2u\\n5. **Mark and return**: \u0110\u1eebng get stuck, mark v\xe0 return sau\\n\\n### After Exam\\n\\n1. **Don\'t panic**: N\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng pass, hi\u1ec3u r\u1eb1ng nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\u1ea7n retake\\n2. **Review your results**: Xem areas c\u1ea7n improve\\n3. **Schedule retake**: N\u1ebfu c\u1ea7n, schedule ngay\\n4. **Keep learning**: Exam l\xe0 milestone, kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc8 K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 Tu\u1ea7n 4\\n\\nSau Tu\u1ea7n 4, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh:\\n\\n- \u2705 **500+ practice questions** (78% accuracy)\\n- \u2705 **3 mock exams** (68%, 72%, 78%)\\n- \u2705 **Comprehensive cheat sheets** cho t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 topics\\n- \u2705 **Final exam**: **85%** \u2705 **PASSED**\\n- \u2705 **Certification achieved!** \ud83c\udf89\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcad Nh\u1eefng b\xe0i h\u1ecdc quan tr\u1ecdng\\n\\n1. **Practice makes perfect**: L\xe0m nhi\u1ec1u questions l\xe0 c\xe1ch t\u1ed1t nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec3 chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb.\\n2. **Understand, don\'t memorize**: Hi\u1ec3u concepts, \u0111\u1eebng ch\u1ec9 nh\u1edb answers.\\n3. **Time management is key**: 105 minutes cho 60 questions, practice \u0111\u1ec3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh.\\n4. **Stay calm**: Nerves c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m b\u1ea1n commit mistakes sai.\\n5. **Review thoroughly**: \u0110\u1eebng submit m\xe0 kh\xf4ng review.\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Sau khi \u0111\u1ea1t ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9\\n\\nB\xe2y gi\u1edd t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c **Salesforce Platform Developer I** certification, k\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch ti\u1ebfp theo l\xe0:\\n\\n- [ ] **Salesforce Platform App Builder** certification\\n- [ ] **Salesforce Platform Developer II** certification\\n- [ ] **Build real-world projects** tr\xean GitHub\\n- [ ] **Contribute to community** (Stack Exchange, GitHub)\\n- [ ] **Continuous learning** - Technology thay \u0111\u1ed5i nhanh!\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcdd L\u1eddi khuy\xean cho b\u1ea1n\\n\\nN\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n \u0111ang chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho Salesforce Platform Developer I exam:\\n\\n1. **Start early**: \u0110\u1eebng ch\u1edd \u0111\u1ebfn tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u.\\n2. **Use Focus on Force**: N\xf3 l\xe0 resource t\u1ed1t nh\u1ea5t.\\n3. **Practice questions**: L\xe0m c\xe0ng nhi\u1ec1u c\xe0ng t\u1ed1t.\\n4. **Create cheat sheets**: N\xf3 gi\xfap review nhanh tr\u01b0\u1edbc exam.\\n5. **Stay consistent**: H\u1ecdc m\u1ed7i ng\xe0y, kh\xf4ng binge-study.\\n6. **Don\'t give up**: Nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\u1ea7n retake, \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 b\xecnh th\u01b0\u1eddng.\\n7. **Believe in yourself**: B\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c!\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Ch\xfac b\u1ea1n may m\u1eafn v\u1edbi k\u1ef3 thi c\u1ee7a m\xecnh!** \ud83c\udf40\\n\\nB\u1ea1n c\xf3 c\xe2u h\u1ecfi g\xec v\u1ec1 exam preparation? H\xe3y \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea1i b\xecnh lu\u1eadn b\xean d\u01b0\u1edbi! \ud83d\udcac\\n\\n**Tags**: #Salesforce #PlatformDeveloperI #ExamPrep #Certification #Tips #Success"},{"id":"bat-dau-voi-lwc","metadata":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/bat-dau-voi-lwc","editUrl":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce/tree/main/website/blog/blog/2026-02-08-bat-dau-voi-lwc.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-08-bat-dau-voi-lwc.md","title":"B\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u v\u1edbi LWC: Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c trong Tu\u1ea7n 3","description":"Tu\u1ea7n 3 l\xe0 khi t\xf4i kh\xe1m ph\xe1 Lightning Web Components (LWC) - c\xf4ng ngh\u1ec7 hi\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea1i nh\u1ea5t c\u1ee7a Salesforce \u0111\u1ec3 x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng giao di\u1ec7n ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng. LWC s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng web standards (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) v\xe0 r\u1ea5t kh\xe1c bi\u1ec7t v\u1edbi c\xe1c framework c\u0169 nh\u01b0 Visualforce hay Aura.","date":"2026-02-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"tuan-3","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/tuan-3"},{"inline":true,"label":"lwc","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/lwc"},{"inline":true,"label":"frontend","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/frontend"},{"inline":true,"label":"javascript","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/javascript"},{"inline":true,"label":"bat-dau","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/bat-dau"}],"readingTime":7.25,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"H\u1ecdc L\u1ea1i","title":"Salesforce Platform Developer I Learner","url":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce","page":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/authors/hoclai"},"description":"Chia s\u1ebb h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 kinh nghi\u1ec7m v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497.png","key":"hoclai"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"bat-dau-voi-lwc","title":"B\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u v\u1edbi LWC: Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c trong Tu\u1ea7n 3","authors":["hoclai"],"tags":["tuan-3","lwc","frontend","javascript","bat-dau"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Tu\u1ea7n cu\u1ed1i tr\u01b0\u1edbc k\u1ef3 thi: Chi\u1ebfn l\u01b0\u1ee3c \xf4n t\u1eadp c\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ed9 cao","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tuan-cuoi-truoc-ky-thi"},"nextItem":{"title":"Apex cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u: H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau"}},"content":"Tu\u1ea7n 3 l\xe0 khi t\xf4i kh\xe1m ph\xe1 **Lightning Web Components (LWC)** - c\xf4ng ngh\u1ec7 hi\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea1i nh\u1ea5t c\u1ee7a Salesforce \u0111\u1ec3 x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng giao di\u1ec7n ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng. LWC s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng web standards (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) v\xe0 r\u1ea5t kh\xe1c bi\u1ec7t v\u1edbi c\xe1c framework c\u0169 nh\u01b0 Visualforce hay Aura.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf LWC l\xe0 g\xec?\\n\\nLWC (Lightning Web Component) l\xe0:\\n- **Lightweight**: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng web standards, kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n framework n\u1eb7ng\\n- **Modern**: D\u1ef1a tr\xean c\xe1c web standards m\u1edbi nh\u1ea5t\\n- **Secure**: Theo Salesforce security model\\n- **Fast**: T\u1ed1i \u01b0u hi\u1ec7u n\u0103ng, load nhanh\\n\\n### LWC vs Aura vs Visualforce\\n\\n```\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502         Salesforce UI Technologies              \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 Visualforce (2005)                              \u2502\\n\u2502 - Server-side rendering                         \u2502\\n\u2502 - VF pages + Apex controllers                  \u2502\\n\u2502 - Legacy, kh\xf4ng khuy\u1ebfn ngh\u1ecb cho projects m\u1edbi    \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 Aura Components (2014)                         \u2502\\n\u2502 - Client-side, component-based                  \u2502\\n\u2502 - Framework ri\xeang c\u1ee7a Salesforce               \u2502\\n\u2502 - \u0110\u01b0\u1ee3c h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 nh\u01b0ng kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i focus           \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 Lightning Web Components (2018) \u2705 RECOMMENDED \u2502\\n\u2502 - Web standards (Custom Elements)              \u2502\\n\u2502 - Modern JavaScript (ES6+)                     \u2502\\n\u2502 - Lightning Data Service                        \u2502\\n\u2502 - T\u01b0\u01a1ng th\xedch v\u1edbi Aura                          \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc1 C\u1ea5u tr\xfac c\u1ee7a m\u1ed9t LWC Component\\n\\nM\u1ed9t LWC component bao g\u1ed3m 3 files ch\xednh:\\n\\n```\\nmyComponent/\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 myComponent.html       # Template (HTML)\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 myComponent.js         # Controller (JavaScript)\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 myComponent.css        # Styles (CSS - optional)\\n```\\n\\n### V\xed d\u1ee5: Hello World Component\\n\\n**myComponent.html**\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    <lightning-card title=\\"Hello World\\" icon-name=\\"standard:account\\">\\n        <div class=\\"slds-m-around_medium\\">\\n            <p>Xin ch\xe0o, {greeting}!</p>\\n            <lightning-button \\n                label=\\"Click Me\\" \\n                onclick={handleClick}>\\n            </lightning-button>\\n        </div>\\n    </lightning-card>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n**myComponent.js**\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement, track } from \'lwc\';\\n\\nexport default class MyComponent extends LightningElement {\\n    @track greeting = \'Salesforce Developer\';\\n    \\n    handleClick() {\\n        this.greeting = \'Button clicked!\';\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**myComponent.css**\\n```css\\np {\\n    color: #0070d2;\\n    font-size: 18px;\\n    font-weight: bold;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd11 C\xe1c kh\xe1i ni\u1ec7m quan tr\u1ecdng trong LWC\\n\\n### 1. Reactive Properties\\n\\nS\u1eed d\u1ee5ng `@track` v\xe0 `@api` \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ea1o reactive properties.\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement, track, api } from \'lwc\';\\n\\nexport default class ReactiveExample extends LightningElement {\\n    // @track: Property t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng re-render khi thay \u0111\u1ed5i\\n    @track counter = 0;\\n    \\n    // @api: Public property, c\xf3 th\u1ec3 nh\u1eadn t\u1eeb parent\\n    @api title = \'Default Title\';\\n    \\n    increment() {\\n        this.counter++; // T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng re-render UI\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**L\u01b0u \xfd**: Trong c\xe1c version m\u1edbi c\u1ee7a LWC, t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 properties \u0111\u1ec1u reactive, `@track` kh\xf4ng c\xf2n c\u1ea7n thi\u1ebft.\\n\\n### 2. Lifecycle Hooks\\n\\nLWC c\xf3 c\xe1c lifecycle hooks \u0111\u1ec3 qu\u1ea3n l\xfd component lifecycle:\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement } from \'lwc\';\\n\\nexport default class LifecycleExample extends LightningElement {\\n    constructor() {\\n        super();\\n        console.log(\'Constructor called\');\\n    }\\n    \\n    connectedCallback() {\\n        // Ch\u1ea1y khi component \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\xeam v\xe0o DOM\\n        console.log(\'Component connected\');\\n        // T\u1ed1t cho: Load data, subscribe to events\\n    }\\n    \\n    disconnectedCallback() {\\n        // Ch\u1ea1y khi component \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c x\xf3a kh\u1ecfi DOM\\n        console.log(\'Component disconnected\');\\n        // T\u1ed1t cho: Cleanup, unsubscribe\\n    }\\n    \\n    renderedCallback() {\\n        // Ch\u1ea1y m\u1ed7i khi component re-renders\\n        console.log(\'Component rendered\');\\n        // C\u1ea9n th\u1eadn: C\xf3 th\u1ec3 g\xe2y infinite loop n\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng c\u1ea9n th\u1eadn\\n    }\\n    \\n    errorCallback(error, stack) {\\n        // Ch\u1ea1y khi c\xf3 error trong component\\n        console.error(\'Error:\', error);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Communication gi\u1eefa Components\\n\\n#### Parent to Child (s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng properties)\\n\\n**ParentComponent.html**\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    <c-child-component title=\\"Hello from Parent\\"></c-child-component>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n**ChildComponent.js**\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement, api } from \'lwc\';\\n\\nexport default class ChildComponent extends LightningElement {\\n    @api title; // Nh\u1eadn title t\u1eeb parent\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### Child to Parent (s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Custom Events)\\n\\n**ChildComponent.js**\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement } from \'lwc\';\\n\\nexport default class ChildComponent extends LightningElement {\\n    handleClick() {\\n        // Create custom event\\n        const selectedEvent = new CustomEvent(\'itemselected\', {\\n            detail: { itemId: \'123\', itemName: \'My Item\' }\\n        });\\n        \\n        // Dispatch event\\n        this.dispatchEvent(selectedEvent);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**ParentComponent.js**\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement } from \'lwc\';\\n\\nexport default class ParentComponent extends LightningElement {\\n    handleItemSelected(event) {\\n        const itemId = event.detail.itemId;\\n        const itemName = event.detail.itemName;\\n        console.log(`Selected: ${itemName} (${itemId})`);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**ParentComponent.html**\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    <c-child-component onitemselected={handleItemSelected}></c-child-component>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n#### Sibling Components (s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Lightning Message Service)\\n\\n```javascript\\n// Component A g\u1eedi message\\nimport { publish, MessageContext } from \'lightning/messageService\';\\nimport myMessageChannel from \'@salesforce/messageChannel/MyMessageChannel__c\';\\n\\nexport default class ComponentA extends LightningElement {\\n    @wire(MessageContext) messageContext;\\n    \\n    sendMessage() {\\n        publish(this.messageContext, myMessageChannel, {\\n            recordId: \'001xx000003DGb2AAG\',\\n            message: \'Hello from Component A\'\\n        });\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n// Component B nh\u1eadn message\\nimport { subscribe, MessageContext, unsubscribe } from \'lightning/messageService\';\\nimport myMessageChannel from \'@salesforce/messageChannel/MyMessageChannel__c\';\\n\\nexport default class ComponentB extends LightningElement {\\n    @wire(MessageContext) messageContext;\\n    subscription;\\n    \\n    connectedCallback() {\\n        this.subscribeToMessageChannel();\\n    }\\n    \\n    subscribeToMessageChannel() {\\n        this.subscription = subscribe(\\n            this.messageContext,\\n            myMessageChannel,\\n            (message) => this.handleMessage(message)\\n        );\\n    }\\n    \\n    handleMessage(message) {\\n        console.log(\'Received:\', message.message);\\n    }\\n    \\n    disconnectedCallback() {\\n        unsubscribe(this.subscription);\\n        this.subscription = null;\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca Lightning Data Service (LDS)\\n\\nLDS cho ph\xe9p b\u1ea1n truy c\u1eadp v\xe0 manipulate Salesforce data m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n Apex controller.\\n\\n### wire service v\u1edbi LDS\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement, wire, track } from \'lwc\';\\nimport { getRecord, getFieldValue } from \'lightning/uiRecordApi\';\\nimport ACCOUNT_NAME_FIELD from \'@salesforce/schema/Account.Name\';\\nimport ACCOUNT_INDUSTRY_FIELD from \'@salesforce/schema/Account.Industry\';\\nimport ACCOUNT_ID from \'@salesforce/schema/Account.Id\';\\n\\nconst FIELDS = [ACCOUNT_NAME_FIELD, ACCOUNT_INDUSTRY_FIELD];\\n\\nexport default class AccountViewer extends LightningElement {\\n    @track accountId = \'001xx000003DGb2AAG\'; // Hardcoded ho\u1eb7c t\u1eeb URL\\n    \\n    @wire(getRecord, { recordId: \'$accountId\', fields: FIELDS })\\n    account;\\n    \\n    get name() {\\n        return getFieldValue(this.account.data, ACCOUNT_NAME_FIELD);\\n    }\\n    \\n    get industry() {\\n        return getFieldValue(this.account.data, ACCOUNT_INDUSTRY_FIELD);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**accountViewer.html**\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    <lightning-card title=\\"Account Details\\">\\n        <div class=\\"slds-m-around_medium\\">\\n            <template if:true={account.data}>\\n                <p><strong>Name:</strong> {name}</p>\\n                <p><strong>Industry:</strong> {industry}</p>\\n            </template>\\n            \\n            <template if:true={account.error}>\\n                <p>Error loading account data</p>\\n            </template>\\n        </div>\\n    </lightning-card>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n### Imperative LDS methods\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement, wire } from \'lwc\';\\nimport { createRecord } from \'lightning/uiRecordApi\';\\nimport ACCOUNT_OBJECT from \'@salesforce/schema/Account\';\\nimport ACCOUNT_NAME_FIELD from \'@salesforce/schema/Account.Name\';\\n\\nexport default class AccountCreator extends LightningElement {\\n    accountName = \'\';\\n    \\n    handleNameChange(event) {\\n        this.accountName = event.target.value;\\n    }\\n    \\n    createAccount() {\\n        const fields = {};\\n        fields[ACCOUNT_NAME_FIELD.fieldApiName] = this.accountName;\\n        \\n        const recordInput = { apiName: ACCOUNT_OBJECT.objectApiName, fields };\\n        \\n        createRecord(recordInput)\\n            .then(account => {\\n                console.log(\'Account created:\', account.id);\\n                // Show success message\\n            })\\n            .catch(error => {\\n                console.error(\'Error creating account:\', error);\\n                // Show error message\\n            });\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfa8 Lightning Design System (SLDS)\\n\\nSalesforce cung c\u1ea5p Lightning Design System v\u1edbi c\xe1c components v\xe0 styles \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf s\u1eb5n.\\n\\n### S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Lightning Components\\n\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    \x3c!-- Card --\x3e\\n    <lightning-card title=\\"Account Information\\">\\n        \x3c!-- Input fields --\x3e\\n        <lightning-input \\n            label=\\"Account Name\\" \\n            value={accountName}\\n            onchange={handleNameChange}>\\n        </lightning-input>\\n        \\n        \x3c!-- Button --\x3e\\n        <lightning-button \\n            variant=\\"brand\\"\\n            label=\\"Save\\"\\n            onclick={handleSave}>\\n        </lightning-button>\\n        \\n        \x3c!-- DataTable --\x3e\\n        <lightning-datatable\\n            key-field=\\"id\\"\\n            data={data}\\n            columns={columns}>\\n        </lightning-datatable>\\n    </lightning-card>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd17 Integration v\u1edbi Apex\\n\\nKhi LDS kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ee7, b\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 g\u1ecdi Apex methods t\u1eeb LWC.\\n\\n### Apex Controller\\n\\n```apex\\npublic with sharing class AccountController {\\n    @AuraEnabled(cacheable=true)\\n    public static List<Account> getAccounts(String industry) {\\n        return [SELECT Id, Name, Industry, AnnualRevenue \\n                FROM Account \\n                WHERE Industry = :industry \\n                LIMIT 10];\\n    }\\n    \\n    @AuraEnabled\\n    public static Account createAccount(Account acc) {\\n        insert acc;\\n        return acc;\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### LWC Component\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { LightningElement, wire, track } from \'lwc\';\\nimport getAccounts from \'@salesforce/apex/AccountController.getAccounts\';\\nimport createAccount from \'@salesforce/apex/AccountController.createAccount\';\\n\\nexport default class AccountManager extends LightningElement {\\n    @track industry = \'Technology\';\\n    @track accounts = [];\\n    @track error;\\n    \\n    // Wire service\\n    @wire(getAccounts, { industry: \'$industry\' })\\n    wiredAccounts({ error, data }) {\\n        if (data) {\\n            this.accounts = data;\\n            this.error = undefined;\\n        } else if (error) {\\n            this.error = error;\\n            this.accounts = undefined;\\n        }\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Imperative call\\n    handleCreateAccount() {\\n        const acc = {\\n            Name: \'New Account\',\\n            Industry: this.industry\\n        };\\n        \\n        createAccount({ acc: acc })\\n            .then(result => {\\n                console.log(\'Account created:\', result.Id);\\n                // Refresh data\\n                refreshApex(this.wiredAccounts);\\n            })\\n            .catch(error => {\\n                console.error(\'Error:\', error);\\n            });\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udca1 Best Practices t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c\\n\\n### 1. T\xe1ch logic kh\u1ecfi template\\n\\n```javascript\\n// \u274c BAD: Logic trong template\\n<template>\\n    <p>{account.Industry === \'Technology\' ? \'Tech\' : \'Other\'}</p>\\n</template>\\n\\n// \u2705 GOOD: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng getter\\n<template>\\n    <p>{industryLabel}</p>\\n</template>\\n\\n// Trong .js file\\nget industryLabel() {\\n    return this.account.Industry === \'Technology\' ? \'Tech\' : \'Other\';\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng template conditionals thay v\xec JS conditionals\\n\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    \x3c!-- \u2705 GOOD: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng if:true/if:false --\x3e\\n    <template if:true={showMessage}>\\n        <p>This is shown when showMessage is true</p>\\n    </template>\\n    \\n    <template if:false={showMessage}>\\n        <p>This is shown when showMessage is false</p>\\n    </template>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Tr\xe1nh tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp manipulate DOM\\n\\n```javascript\\n// \u274c BAD: Manipulate DOM tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp\\nhandleClick() {\\n    const element = this.template.querySelector(\'.my-element\');\\n    element.style.display = \'none\';\\n}\\n\\n// \u2705 GOOD: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng reactive property\\nhandleClick() {\\n    this.isVisible = false;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n```html\\n<template>\\n    <div class=\\"my-element\\" if:true={isVisible}>\\n        Content here\\n    </div>\\n</template>\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Handle l\u1ed7i m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch graceful\\n\\n```javascript\\n@wire(getData)\\nwiredData({ error, data }) {\\n    if (data) {\\n        this.data = data;\\n        this.error = undefined;\\n    } else if (error) {\\n        this.data = undefined;\\n        this.error = error;\\n        console.error(\'Error loading data:\', error);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddea Testing LWC v\u1edbi Jest\\n\\n```javascript\\n// accountViewer.test.js\\nimport { createElement } from \'lwc\';\\nimport AccountViewer from \'c/accountViewer\';\\n\\ndescribe(\'c-account-viewer\', () => {\\n    it(\'displays account name when data is loaded\', () => {\\n        // Create element\\n        const element = createElement(\'c-account-viewer\', {\\n            is: AccountViewer\\n        });\\n        document.body.appendChild(element);\\n        \\n        // Emit mock data\\n        const mockGetRecord = require(\'./data/getAccount.json\');\\n        getRecord.emit(mockGetRecord);\\n        \\n        // Return a promise to wait for reactive updates\\n        return Promise.resolve().then(() => {\\n            const nameElement = element.shadowRoot.querySelector(\'p\');\\n            expect(nameElement.textContent).toBe(mockGetRecord.fields.Name.value);\\n        });\\n    });\\n});\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc8 K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 Tu\u1ea7n 3\\n\\nSau Tu\u1ea7n 3, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh:\\n\\n- \u2705 **8 LWC Components** v\u1edbi ch\u1ee9c n\u0103ng kh\xe1c nhau\\n- \u2705 **Revenue Dashboard** v\u1edbi Chart.js integration\\n- \u2705 **Lightning Data Service** cho data access\\n- \u2705 **Apex integration** cho complex logic\\n- \u2705 **5 Jest Tests** v\u1edbi 80%+ coverage\\n- \u2705 **Event communication** gi\u1eefa components\\n- \u2705 **SLDS components** cho UI \u0111\u1eb9p\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcad Nh\u1eefng b\xe0i h\u1ecdc quan tr\u1ecdng\\n\\n1. **Think in components**: Chia nh\u1ecf UI th\xe0nh c\xe1c components c\xf3 th\u1ec3 t\xe1i s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng.\\n2. **LDS first**: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Lightning Data Service tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi vi\u1ebft Apex.\\n3. **Reactive programming**: Hi\u1ec3u r\xf5 khi n\xe0o data thay \u0111\u1ed5i v\xe0 UI re-renders.\\n4. **Test your components**: Jest tests gi\xfap \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o quality.\\n5. **Learn SLDS**: Lightning Design System gi\xfap UI \u0111\u1eb9p v\xe0 consistent.\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho Tu\u1ea7n 4\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 4 l\xe0 giai \u0111o\u1ea1n quan tr\u1ecdng nh\u1ea5t - **Luy\u1ec7n thi v\xe0 Intensive Review**. T\xf4i s\u1ebd:\\n- L\xe0m 500+ c\xe2u h\u1ecfi practice\\n- H\u1ecdc s\xe2u v\u1ec1 Governor Limits\\n- T\u1ea1o exam cheat sheets\\n- L\xe0m 3+ practice exams\\n\\n---\\n\\n**B\xe0i vi\u1ebft ti\u1ebfp theo**: [X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng Dashboard Doanh thu v\u1edbi Chart.js](#) (coming soon)\\n\\nB\u1ea1n c\xf3 c\xe2u h\u1ecfi g\xec v\u1ec1 LWC? H\xe3y \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea1i b\xecnh lu\u1eadn b\xean d\u01b0\u1edbi! \ud83d\udcac\\n\\n**Tags**: #Salesforce #PlatformDeveloperI #LWC #Lightning #Frontend #JavaScript"},{"id":"apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau","metadata":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau","editUrl":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce/tree/main/website/blog/blog/2026-02-01-apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-01-apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau.md","title":"Apex cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u: H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh","description":"Tu\u1ea7n 2 l\xe0 khi t\xf4i th\u1ef1c s\u1ef1 b\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0o th\u1ebf gi\u1edbi l\u1eadp tr\xecnh Salesforce v\u1edbi Apex. \u0110\xe2y l\xe0 ng\xf4n ng\u1eef backend ch\xednh th\u1ee9c c\u1ee7a Salesforce, r\u1ea5t gi\u1ed1ng Java. Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c v\u1ec1 Apex t\u1eeb con s\u1ed1 kh\xf4ng.","date":"2026-02-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"tuan-2","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/tuan-2"},{"inline":true,"label":"apex","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/apex"},{"inline":true,"label":"lap-trinh","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/lap-trinh"},{"inline":true,"label":"backend","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/backend"},{"inline":true,"label":"bat-dau","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/bat-dau"}],"readingTime":7.39,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"H\u1ecdc L\u1ea1i","title":"Salesforce Platform Developer I Learner","url":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce","page":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/authors/hoclai"},"description":"Chia s\u1ebb h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 kinh nghi\u1ec7m v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497.png","key":"hoclai"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau","title":"Apex cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u: H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh","authors":["hoclai"],"tags":["tuan-2","apex","lap-trinh","backend","bat-dau"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"B\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u v\u1edbi LWC: Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c trong Tu\u1ea7n 3","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/bat-dau-voi-lwc"},"nextItem":{"title":"X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng \u1ee8ng d\u1ee5ng Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd D\u1ef1 \xe1n: M\u1eb9o v\xe0 Th\u1ee7 thu\u1eadt","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/xay-dung-project-management-app"}},"content":"Tu\u1ea7n 2 l\xe0 khi t\xf4i th\u1ef1c s\u1ef1 b\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0o th\u1ebf gi\u1edbi l\u1eadp tr\xecnh Salesforce v\u1edbi **Apex**. \u0110\xe2y l\xe0 ng\xf4n ng\u1eef backend ch\xednh th\u1ee9c c\u1ee7a Salesforce, r\u1ea5t gi\u1ed1ng Java. Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c v\u1ec1 Apex t\u1eeb con s\u1ed1 kh\xf4ng.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Apex l\xe0 g\xec?\\n\\nApex l\xe0 m\u1ed9t ng\xf4n ng\u1eef l\u1eadp tr\xecnh:\\n- Strongly-typed (ki\u1ec3m tra ki\u1ec3u d\u1eef li\u1ec7u nghi\xeam ng\u1eb7t)\\n- Object-oriented (h\u01b0\u1edbng \u0111\u1ed1i t\u01b0\u1ee3ng)\\n- Runs on Salesforce servers (server-side)\\n- Resembles Java syntax\\n\\n### Khi n\xe0o d\xf9ng Apex?\\n\\n```\\n\u2705 D\xf9ng Apex khi:\\n- Business logic qu\xe1 ph\u1ee9c t\u1ea1p cho Flow\\n- C\u1ea7n x\u1eed l\xfd h\xe0ng ng\xe0n records (bulk operations)\\n- C\u1ea7n call external APIs\\n- C\u1ea7n custom validation logic ph\u1ee9c t\u1ea1p\\n- C\u1ea7n integration v\u1edbi c\xe1c h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng kh\xe1c\\n\\n\u274c KH\xd4NG d\xf9ng Apex khi:\\n- Flow c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c (Flow d\u1ec5 maintain h\u01a1n)\\n- Nhi\u1ec7m v\u1ee5 \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n (Formula field \u0111\u1ee7)\\n- Ch\u1ec9 c\u1ea7n CRUD operations (standard features)\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcda C\u1ea5u tr\xfac c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n c\u1ee7a Apex\\n\\n### 1. Variables & Data Types\\n\\n```apex\\n// Primitive Types\\nInteger i = 10;\\nDecimal d = 10.5;\\nBoolean isActive = true;\\nString name = \'Salesforce\';\\nDate todayDate = Date.today();\\nDateTime now = DateTime.now();\\nID accountId = \'001xx000003DGb2AAG\';\\n\\n// Collections\\nList<String> names = new List<String>{\'John\', \'Jane\', \'Bob\'};\\nSet<Integer> uniqueNumbers = new Set<Integer>{1, 2, 3, 3}; // {1, 2, 3}\\nMap<String, Integer> scores = new Map<String, Integer>();\\nscores.put(\'John\', 95);\\nscores.put(\'Jane\', 87);\\n\\n// SOQL Query Results\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 10];\\n\\n// sObjects (Salesforce Objects)\\nAccount acc = new Account();\\nacc.Name = \'Test Account\';\\nacc.BillingCity = \'Ho Chi Minh City\';\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Control Flow\\n\\n```apex\\n// If-Else\\nInteger score = 85;\\nif (score >= 90) {\\n    System.debug(\'Grade: A\');\\n} else if (score >= 80) {\\n    System.debug(\'Grade: B\');\\n} else {\\n    System.debug(\'Grade: C or lower\');\\n}\\n\\n// For Loop\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 10];\\nfor (Account acc : accounts) {\\n    System.debug(\'Account: \' + acc.Name);\\n}\\n\\n// For Loop v\u1edbi index\\nfor (Integer i = 0; i < accounts.size(); i++) {\\n    System.debug(\'Account \' + i + \': \' + accounts[i].Name);\\n}\\n\\n// While Loop\\nInteger count = 0;\\nwhile (count < 5) {\\n    System.debug(\'Count: \' + count);\\n    count++;\\n}\\n\\n// Do-While Loop\\ndo {\\n    System.debug(\'At least once\');\\n} while (false);\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Classes & Methods\\n\\n```apex\\npublic class AccountManager {\\n    // Instance variable\\n    private String currentUserId;\\n    \\n    // Constructor\\n    public AccountManager() {\\n        this.currentUserId = UserInfo.getUserId();\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Public method\\n    public List<Account> getActiveAccounts() {\\n        List<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name \\n                                    FROM Account \\n                                    WHERE Active__c = true];\\n        return accounts;\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Private method\\n    private void validateAccount(Account acc) {\\n        if (String.isBlank(acc.Name)) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\'Account name is required\');\\n        }\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Static method\\n    public static Account createAccount(String name, String industry) {\\n        Account acc = new Account(\\n            Name = name,\\n            Industry = industry\\n        );\\n        return acc;\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n// S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng class\\nAccountManager manager = new AccountManager();\\nList<Account> accounts = manager.getActiveAccounts();\\n\\nAccount newAcc = AccountManager.createAccount(\\n    \'New Account\', \\n    \'Technology\'\\n);\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd25 SOQL: Salesforce Object Query Language\\n\\nSOQL t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 SQL nh\u01b0ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf cho Salesforce data.\\n\\n### C\u01a1 b\u1ea3n v\u1ec1 SOQL\\n\\n```apex\\n// SELECT basics\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name, Industry \\n                            FROM Account \\n                            WHERE Industry = \'Technology\'];\\n\\n// SELECT v\u1edbi LIMIT\\nList<Account> topAccounts = [SELECT Id, Name \\n                              FROM Account \\n                              ORDER BY CreatedDate DESC \\n                              LIMIT 5];\\n\\n// SELECT v\u1edbi AND/OR\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name \\n                            FROM Account \\n                            WHERE (Industry = \'Technology\' \\n                                   OR Industry = \'Finance\')\\n                            AND BillingState = \'CA\'];\\n\\n// SELECT v\u1edbi relationship fields\\nList<Contact> contacts = [SELECT Id, Name, Account.Name, Account.Industry \\n                          FROM Contact \\n                          WHERE Account.Industry = \'Technology\'];\\n\\n// SELECT v\u1edbi LIKE\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name \\n                            FROM Account \\n                            WHERE Name LIKE \'%Inc%\'];\\n\\n// SELECT v\u1edbi child relationships (subqueries)\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name, \\n                                  (SELECT Id, FirstName, LastName \\n                                   FROM Contacts \\n                                   ORDER BY LastName)\\n                            FROM Account \\n                            WHERE Id = :accountId];\\n```\\n\\n### DML Operations\\n\\n```apex\\n// INSERT\\nAccount newAccount = new Account(\\n    Name = \'Test Account\',\\n    Industry = \'Technology\'\\n);\\ninsert newAccount;\\nSystem.debug(\'New Account ID: \' + newAccount.Id);\\n\\n// UPDATE\\nAccount acc = [SELECT Id, Name, Industry \\n               FROM Account \\n               WHERE Name = \'Test Account\' \\n               LIMIT 1];\\nacc.Industry = \'Finance\';\\nupdate acc;\\n\\n// DELETE\\nAccount accToDelete = [SELECT Id FROM Account WHERE Name = \'Test Account\' LIMIT 1];\\ndelete accToDelete;\\n\\n// UPSERT (Update ho\u1eb7c Insert)\\nAccount acc = new Account(\\n    Name = \'Unique Account Name\',\\n    External_Id__c = \'UNIQUE123\'\\n);\\nupsert acc External_Id__c;\\n\\n// Bulk Operations\\nList<Account> accountsToInsert = new List<Account>();\\nfor (Integer i = 0; i < 100; i++) {\\n    accountsToInsert.add(new Account(Name = \'Account \' + i));\\n}\\ninsert accountsToInsert; // Ch\u1ec9 1 DML statement!\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Apex Triggers\\n\\nTriggers t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\u1ea1y khi record \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o, c\u1eadp nh\u1eadt, ho\u1eb7c x\xf3a.\\n\\n### C\u1ea5u tr\xfac Trigger\\n\\n```apex\\ntrigger AccountTrigger on Account (\\n    before insert, \\n    before update, \\n    after insert, \\n    after update, \\n    before delete, \\n    after delete\\n) {\\n    // Logic \u1edf \u0111\xe2y\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### V\xed d\u1ee5 th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf: Prevent Account Deletion\\n\\n```apex\\ntrigger AccountDeletionPreventer on Account (before delete) {\\n    for (Account acc : Trigger.old) {\\n        // Prevent deletion if account has opportunities\\n        List<Opportunity> opps = [SELECT Id \\n                                   FROM Opportunity \\n                                   WHERE AccountId = :acc.Id \\n                                   LIMIT 1];\\n        if (!opps.isEmpty()) {\\n            acc.addError(\'Kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 x\xf3a Account c\xf3 Opportunities li\xean quan\');\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### V\xed d\u1ee5: Auto-populate fields\\n\\n```apex\\ntrigger AccountAutoUpdate on Account (before insert, before update) {\\n    for (Account acc : Trigger.new) {\\n        // Set default industry if not specified\\n        if (acc.Industry == null) {\\n            acc.Industry = \'Other\';\\n        }\\n        \\n        // Auto-populate description\\n        if (String.isBlank(acc.Description)) {\\n            acc.Description = \'Created on \' + Date.today().format();\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Best Practices cho Triggers\\n\\n```apex\\n// \u274c BAD: Logic trong trigger\\ntrigger AccountTrigger on Account (before insert) {\\n    for (Account acc : Trigger.new) {\\n        // 100+ d\xf2ng logic \u1edf \u0111\xe2y = KH\xd4NG T\u1ed0T\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n// \u2705 GOOD: G\u1ecdi handler class\\ntrigger AccountTrigger on Account (before insert, before update) {\\n    AccountTriggerHandler handler = new AccountTriggerHandler();\\n    if (Trigger.isInsert) {\\n        handler.onBeforeInsert(Trigger.new);\\n    } else if (Trigger.isUpdate) {\\n        handler.onBeforeUpdate(Trigger.old, Trigger.new);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddea Apex Testing\\n\\nSalesforce y\xeau c\u1ea7u **75% code coverage** \u0111\u1ec3 deploy code l\xean production.\\n\\n### C\u1ea5u tr\xfac Test Class\\n\\n```apex\\n@isTest\\nprivate class AccountManagerTest {\\n    \\n    // Test setup method (ch\u1ea1y tr\u01b0\u1edbc m\u1ed7i test method)\\n    @testSetup\\n    static void setupData() {\\n        List<Account> accounts = new List<Account>();\\n        for (Integer i = 0; i < 10; i++) {\\n            accounts.add(new Account(\\n                Name = \'Test Account \' + i,\\n                Industry = \'Technology\'\\n            ));\\n        }\\n        insert accounts;\\n    }\\n    \\n    @isTest\\n    static void testGetActiveAccounts() {\\n        // Test logic \u1edf \u0111\xe2y\\n        AccountManager manager = new AccountManager();\\n        List<Account> accounts = manager.getActiveAccounts();\\n        \\n        // Assertions\\n        System.assertEquals(10, accounts.size(), \'Should return 10 accounts\');\\n    }\\n    \\n    @isTest\\n    static void testCreateAccount() {\\n        Test.startTest();\\n        Account acc = AccountManager.createAccount(\'Test\', \'Finance\');\\n        Test.stopTest();\\n        \\n        System.assertNotEquals(null, acc.Id, \'Account should be created\');\\n        System.assertEquals(\'Finance\', acc.Industry, \'Industry should be Finance\');\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Test Triggers\\n\\n```apex\\n@isTest\\nprivate class AccountTriggerTest {\\n    \\n    @isTest\\n    static void testPreventAccountDeletionWithOpportunities() {\\n        // Setup\\n        Account acc = new Account(Name = \'Test Account\');\\n        insert acc;\\n        \\n        Opportunity opp = new Opportunity(\\n            Name = \'Test Opportunity\',\\n            AccountId = acc.Id,\\n            StageName = \'Prospecting\',\\n            CloseDate = Date.today().addDays(30)\\n        );\\n        insert opp;\\n        \\n        // Test\\n        Test.startTest();\\n        try {\\n            delete acc;\\n            System.assert(false, \'Should have thrown exception\');\\n        } catch (DmlException e) {\\n            System.assert(e.getMessage().contains(\'Kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 x\xf3a Account\'));\\n        }\\n        Test.stopTest();\\n    }\\n    \\n    @isTest\\n    static void testAutoPopulateFields() {\\n        Account acc = new Account(Name = \'Test Account\');\\n        insert acc;\\n        \\n        // Query \u0111\u1ec3 verify\\n        Account insertedAcc = [SELECT Industry, Description \\n                               FROM Account \\n                               WHERE Id = :acc.Id \\n                               LIMIT 1];\\n        \\n        System.assertEquals(\'Other\', insertedAcc.Industry);\\n        System.assert(insertedAcc.Description.contains(Date.today().format()));\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udca1 Best Practices t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c\\n\\n### 1. Tr\xe1nh SOQL trong v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p\\n\\n```apex\\n// \u274c BAD: 101 SOQL queries\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 100];\\nfor (Account acc : accounts) {\\n    List<Contact> contacts = [SELECT Id, Name FROM Contact WHERE AccountId = :acc.Id];\\n    // X\u1eed l\xfd contacts\\n}\\n\\n// \u2705 GOOD: 1 SOQL query\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name, \\n                                 (SELECT Id, Name FROM Contacts)\\n                          FROM Account \\n                          LIMIT 100];\\nfor (Account acc : accounts) {\\n    List<Contact> contacts = acc.Contacts;\\n    // X\u1eed l\xfd contacts\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Tr\xe1nh DML trong v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p\\n\\n```apex\\n// \u274c BAD: 150 DML operations\\nList<Account> accounts = new List<Account>();\\nfor (Integer i = 0; i < 100; i++) {\\n    Account acc = new Account(Name = \'Account \' + i);\\n    insert acc; // \u274c BAD\\n}\\n\\n// \u2705 GOOD: 1 DML operation\\nList<Account> accounts = new List<Account>();\\nfor (Integer i = 0; i < 100; i++) {\\n    accounts.add(new Account(Name = \'Account \' + i));\\n}\\ninsert accounts; // \u2705 GOOD - bulkified\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Lu\xf4n ki\u1ec3m tra null\\n\\n```apex\\n// \u274c BAD: C\xf3 th\u1ec3 g\xe2y NullPointerException\\nString name = acc.Name;\\nSystem.debug(name.length());\\n\\n// \u2705 GOOD: Ki\u1ec3m tra null tr\u01b0\u1edbc\\nif (acc != null && acc.Name != null) {\\n    System.debug(acc.Name.length());\\n}\\n\\n// \u2705 EVEN BETTER: D\xf9ng safe navigation operator\\nSystem.debug(acc?.Name?.length());\\n```\\n\\n### 4. S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Describe khi c\u1ea7n\\n\\n```apex\\n// Check n\u1ebfu field t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i\\nif (Schema.sObjectType.Account.fields.Name.isAccessible()) {\\n    Account acc = [SELECT Name FROM Account LIMIT 1];\\n}\\n\\n// Get picklist values\\nList<Schema.PicklistEntry> industries = \\n    Account.Industry.getDescribe().getPicklistValues();\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Debugging Apex\\n\\n### S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng System.debug()\\n\\n```apex\\nAccount acc = [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 1];\\n\\n// Debug \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n\\nSystem.debug(\'Account: \' + acc.Name);\\n\\n// Debug v\u1edbi label\\nSystem.debug(\'Account Name: \' + acc.Name);\\n\\n// Debug collection\\nList<Account> accounts = [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 10];\\nfor (Account a : accounts) {\\n    System.debug(\'Account: \' + a.Name);\\n}\\n\\n// Debug v\u1edbi JSON (r\u1ea5t h\u1eefu \xedch)\\nSystem.debug(JSON.serializePretty(acc));\\n```\\n\\n### Debug Logs trong Setup\\n\\n1. V\xe0o **Setup** \u2192 **Debug Logs**\\n2. Th\xeam **User** \u0111\u1ec3 monitor\\n3. Th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n action\\n4. Xem log trong **Debug Logs**\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc8 K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 Tu\u1ea7n 2\\n\\nSau Tu\u1ea7n 2, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh:\\n\\n- \u2705 **5 Apex Classes** v\u1edbi c\xe1c methods kh\xe1c nhau\\n- \u2705 **3 Apex Triggers** cho business logic\\n- \u2705 **10 Test Classes** v\u1edbi 85%+ coverage\\n- \u2705 **20+ SOQL queries** t\u1ed1i \u01b0u\\n- \u2705 **Hi\u1ec3u r\xf5** Governor Limits\\n- \u2705 **Debug skills** t\u1ed1t h\u01a1n\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcad Nh\u1eefng b\xe0i h\u1ecdc quan tr\u1ecdng\\n\\n1. **Bulkify everything**: Lu\xf4n ngh\u0129 v\u1ec1 x\u1eed l\xfd h\xe0ng ng\xe0n records.\\n2. **Test your code**: \u0110\u1eebng deploy n\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng c\xf3 test.\\n3. **Follow best practices**: \u0110\u1eebng vi\u1ebft code \\"just to make it work\\".\\n4. **Debug early**: Debug s\u1edbm h\u01a1n l\xe0 debug sau.\\n5. **Learn from examples**: LWC Recipes v\xe0 Apex Recipes r\u1ea5t h\u1eefu \xedch.\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho Tu\u1ea7n 3\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 3 s\u1ebd t\u1eadp trung v\xe0o **Lightning Web Components (LWC)** - l\u1eadp tr\xecnh frontend. T\xf4i r\u1ea5t h\xe0o h\u1ee9ng v\xec \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 ph\u1ea7n hi\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea1i nh\u1ea5t c\u1ee7a Salesforce!\\n\\n---\\n\\n**B\xe0i vi\u1ebft ti\u1ebfp theo**: [SOQL Queries t\u1eeb C\u01a1 b\u1ea3n \u0111\u1ebfn N\xe2ng cao](#) (coming soon)\\n\\nB\u1ea1n c\xf3 c\xe2u h\u1ecfi g\xec v\u1ec1 Apex? H\xe3y \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea1i b\xecnh lu\u1eadn b\xean d\u01b0\u1edbi! \ud83d\udcac\\n\\n**Tags**: #Salesforce #PlatformDeveloperI #Apex #SOQL #Programming #Backend"},{"id":"xay-dung-project-management-app","metadata":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/xay-dung-project-management-app","editUrl":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce/tree/main/website/blog/blog/2026-01-26-xay-dung-project-management-app.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-26-xay-dung-project-management-app.md","title":"X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng \u1ee8ng d\u1ee5ng Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd D\u1ef1 \xe1n: M\u1eb9o v\xe0 Th\u1ee7 thu\u1eadt","description":"Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb kinh nghi\u1ec7m th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf khi x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng Project Management App - d\u1ef1 \xe1n ch\xednh c\u1ee7a Tu\u1ea7n 1. \u0110\xe2y kh\xf4ng ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t b\xe0i t\u1eadp, m\xe0 l\xe0 c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i \u0111\u1ec3 hi\u1ec3u s\xe2u v\u1ec1 c\xe1ch Salesforce ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng.","date":"2026-01-26T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"tuan-1","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/tuan-1"},{"inline":true,"label":"admin","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/admin"},{"inline":true,"label":"project-app","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/project-app"},{"inline":true,"label":"flow","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/flow"},{"inline":true,"label":"thuc-hanh","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/thuc-hanh"}],"readingTime":6.33,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"H\u1ecdc L\u1ea1i","title":"Salesforce Platform Developer I Learner","url":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce","page":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/authors/hoclai"},"description":"Chia s\u1ebb h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 kinh nghi\u1ec7m v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497.png","key":"hoclai"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"xay-dung-project-management-app","title":"X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng \u1ee8ng d\u1ee5ng Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd D\u1ef1 \xe1n: M\u1eb9o v\xe0 Th\u1ee7 thu\u1eadt","authors":["hoclai"],"tags":["tuan-1","admin","project-app","flow","thuc-hanh"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Apex cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u: H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/apex-cho-nguoi-moi-bat-dau"},"nextItem":{"title":"H\xe0nh tr\xecnh Tu\u1ea7n 1: L\xe0m ch\u1ee7 Qu\u1ea3n tr\u1ecb Salesforce","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/hanh-trinh-tuan-1-admin-flow"}},"content":"Trong b\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y, t\xf4i s\u1ebd chia s\u1ebb kinh nghi\u1ec7m th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf khi x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng **Project Management App** - d\u1ef1 \xe1n ch\xednh c\u1ee7a Tu\u1ea7n 1. \u0110\xe2y kh\xf4ng ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t b\xe0i t\u1eadp, m\xe0 l\xe0 c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i \u0111\u1ec3 hi\u1ec3u s\xe2u v\u1ec1 c\xe1ch Salesforce ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf T\u1ed5ng quan v\u1ec1 Project Management App\\n\\nM\u1ee5c ti\xeau c\u1ee7a app l\xe0 qu\u1ea3n l\xfd d\u1ef1 \xe1n v\u1edbi c\xe1c t\xednh n\u0103ng:\\n\\n- \u2705 Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd Projects v\xe0 Tasks\\n- \u2705 Theo d\xf5i Milestones\\n- \u2705 T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng h\xf3a th\xf4ng b\xe1o v\u1edbi Flow\\n- \u2705 B\xe1o c\xe1o v\xe0 Dashboard\\n- \u2705 Security ph\xf9 h\u1ee3p\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca Thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf Data Model\\n\\n### Objects \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o\\n\\n1. **Project__c** (Custom Object)\\n   - Name: T\xean d\u1ef1 \xe1n\\n   - Description__c: M\xf4 t\u1ea3\\n   - Start_Date__c: Ng\xe0y b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u\\n   - End_Date__c: Ng\xe0y k\u1ebft th\xfac\\n   - Status__c: Tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i (Picklist)\\n   - Budget__c: Ng\xe2n s\xe1ch\\n\\n2. **Task__c** (Custom Object)\\n   - Name: T\xean task\\n   - Description__c: M\xf4 t\u1ea3 chi ti\u1ebft\\n   - Status__c: Tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i\\n   - Priority__c: \u0110\u1ed9 \u01b0u ti\xean\\n   - Due_Date__c: Ng\xe0y h\u1ebft h\u1ea1n\\n   - Project__c: Lookup \u0111\u1ebfn Project\\n\\n3. **Milestone__c** (Custom Object)\\n   - Name: T\xean milestone\\n   - Target_Date__c: Ng\xe0y m\u1ee5c ti\xeau\\n   - Status__c: Tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i\\n   - Project__c: Lookup \u0111\u1ebfn Project\\n\\n### Relationships\\n\\n```\\nProject__c (Master)\\n  \u251c\u2500\u2500 Task__c (Detail - Master-Detail)\\n  \u2514\u2500\u2500 Milestone__c (Detail - Master-Detail)\\n```\\n\\n**L\u01b0u \xfd quan tr\u1ecdng**: T\xf4i ch\u1ecdn Master-Detail thay v\xec Lookup v\xec:\\n- Task v\xe0 Milestone kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\xf3 Project\\n- C\u1ea7n roll-up summary fields tr\xean Project\\n- C\u1ea7n cascade delete khi Project b\u1ecb x\xf3a\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd10 C\u1ea5u h\xecnh Security\\n\\n### 1. Custom Profile cho Project Managers\\n\\nT\u1ea1o Profile \\"Project Manager\\" v\u1edbi quy\u1ec1n:\\n- **CRUD** tr\xean Project, Task, Milestone\\n- **Read Only** tr\xean Account, Contact\\n- **No Access** tr\xean Opportunity, Campaign\\n\\n### 2. Permission Sets cho c\xe1c vai tr\xf2 kh\xe1c\\n\\n- **Team Members**: Ch\u1ec9 c\xf3 Read tr\xean Projects, Create/Read/Update tr\xean Tasks\\n- **Stakeholders**: Ch\u1ec9 c\xf3 Read tr\xean Projects v\xe0 Milestones\\n\\n### 3. Sharing Rules\\n\\n- **Project Owner Team**: T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng chia s\u1ebb Projects cho\u56e2\u961f\u6210\u5458\\n- **Executive Team**: Read access cho qu\u1ea3n l\xfd c\u1ea5p cao\\n\\n```yaml\\nSharing Strategy:\\n1. Role Hierarchy: M\u1eb7c \u0111\u1ecbnh t\u1eeb Owner l\xean\\n2. Sharing Rules: M\u1edf r\u1ed9ng cho team cross-functional\\n3. Manual Sharing: Khi c\u1ea7n tr\u01b0\u1eddng h\u1ee3p \u0111\u1eb7c bi\u1ec7t\\n```\\n\\n## \u26a1 Flow Automations\\n\\nT\xf4i \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o 7 Flows kh\xe1c nhau. \u0110\xe2y l\xe0 nh\u1eefng c\xe1i quan tr\u1ecdng nh\u1ea5t:\\n\\n### 1. New Project Notification Flow\\n\\n**Type**: Record-Triggered Flow (After Create)\\n\\n**Purpose**: G\u1eedi email cho team khi Project m\u1edbi \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o\\n\\n**Logic**:\\n```\\n1. Trigger khi Project__c \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o\\n2. L\u1ea5y danh s\xe1ch Team Members t\u1eeb Project__c.Team__c\\n3. G\u1eedi email cho t\u1eebng th\xe0nh vi\xean\\n4. L\u01b0u l\u1ecbch s\u1eed g\u1eedi v\xe0o Custom Object: Notification_Log__c\\n```\\n\\n**Code equivalent** (\u0111\u1ec3 tham kh\u1ea3o):\\n```java\\n// Apex equivalent (\u0111\u1ec3 hi\u1ec3u Flow)\\ntrigger ProjectTrigger on Project__c (after insert) {\\n    List<Messaging.SingleEmailMessage> emails = new List<>();\\n    \\n    for(Project__c proj : Trigger.new) {\\n        // T\u1ea1o v\xe0 g\u1eedi email\\n        Messaging.SingleEmailMessage mail = new Messaging.SingleEmailMessage();\\n        // ... logic g\u1eedi email\\n        emails.add(mail);\\n    }\\n    \\n    if(!emails.isEmpty()) {\\n        Messaging.sendEmail(emails);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Task Due Date Reminder Flow\\n\\n**Type**: Scheduled Flow (Runs daily at 8:00 AM)\\n\\n**Purpose**: Nh\u1eafc nh\u1edf Tasks s\u1eafp h\u1ebft h\u1ea1n\\n\\n**Logic**:\\n```\\n1. Query Tasks v\u1edbi:\\n   - Status != \'Completed\'\\n   - Due_Date = Tomorrow\\n2. G\u1eedi email reminder cho Assignee\\n3. C\u1eadp nh\u1eadt Reminder_Sent__c = TRUE\\n```\\n\\n**C\u1ea5u h\xecnh Schedule**:\\n- Start: 2026-01-26\\n- Frequency: Daily\\n- Preferred Start Time: 08:00:00\\n- Timezone: Asia/Saigon\\n\\n### 3. Milestone Progress Flow\\n\\n**Type**: Record-Triggered Flow (After Update)\\n\\n**Purpose**: C\u1eadp nh\u1eadt Progress__c tr\xean Project khi Milestone ho\xe0n th\xe0nh\\n\\n**Logic**:\\n```\\n1. Trigger khi Milestone__c.Status__c = \'Completed\'\\n2. Query t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 Milestones li\xean quan\\n3. T\xednh % Milestones \u0111\xe3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh\\n4. Update Project__c.Progress__c\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca Reports & Dashboards\\n\\n### Reports t\u1ea1o ra\\n\\n1. **Projects by Status Report**\\n   - Group by: Status\\n   - Record count\\n   \\n2. **Tasks Due This Week**\\n   - Filter: Due_Date between Today and Next 7 Days\\n   - Columns: Name, Project, Priority, Due_Date\\n\\n3. **Milestone Progress Report**\\n   - Group by: Project, Status\\n   - Calculate: % Completed\\n\\n### Dashboard: Project Overview\\n\\n```\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502  Total Projects: 15                  \u2502\\n\u2502  Active: 12  Completed: 2  Delayed: 1 \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502  Tasks by Status (Pie Chart)        \u2502\\n\u2502  \u251c\u2500 Not Started: 45%                \u2502\\n\u2502  \u251c\u2500 In Progress: 35%                \u2502\\n\u2502  \u2514\u2500 Completed: 20%                  \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502  Milestone Progress (Bar Chart)     \u2502\\n\u2502  \u251c\u2500 Project A: 75%                  \u2502\\n\u2502  \u251c\u2500 Project B: 50%                  \u2502\\n\u2502  \u2514\u2500 Project C: 25%                  \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502  Recent Activities (Table)          \u2502\\n\u2502  - Project D created                \u2502\\n\u2502  - Task E completed                 \u2502\\n\u2502  - Milestone F delayed              \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udca1 Tips & Tricks Learned\\n\\n### 1. Formula Fields l\xe0 b\u1ea1n\\n\\nT\xf4i \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o c\xe1c Formula Fields h\u1eefu \xedch:\\n\\n```salesforce\\n// Days Remaining on Project\\nIF(\\n  AND(\\n    NOT(ISBLANK(Start_Date__c)),\\n    NOT(ISBLANK(End_Date__c)),\\n    End_Date__c > TODAY()\\n  ),\\n  End_Date__c - TODAY(),\\n  0\\n)\\n\\n// Project Health\\nCASE(\\n  Status__c,\\n  \'On Track\', \'\ud83d\udfe2 On Track\',\\n  \'At Risk\', \'\ud83d\udfe1 At Risk\',\\n  \'Delayed\', \'\ud83d\udd34 Delayed\',\\n  \'Not Started\', \'\u26aa Not Started\',\\n  \'\u26aa Unknown\'\\n)\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Validation Rules l\xe0 c\u1ea7n thi\u1ebft\\n\\nT\u1ea1o Validation Rules \u0111\u1ec3 ng\u0103n ch\u1eb7n d\u1eef li\u1ec7u sai:\\n\\n```salesforce\\n// End Date must be after Start Date\\nAND(\\n  NOT(ISBLANK(Start_Date__c)),\\n  NOT(ISBLANK(End_Date__c)),\\n  End_Date__c < Start_Date__c\\n)\\n\\n// Task Due Date must be within Project timeline\\nAND(\\n  NOT(ISBLANK(Project__r.Start_Date__c)),\\n  NOT(ISBLANK(Project__r.End_Date__c)),\\n  OR(\\n    Due_Date__c < Project__r.Start_Date__c,\\n    Due_Date__c > Project__r.End_Date__c\\n  )\\n)\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Debug Flow hi\u1ec7u qu\u1ea3\\n\\nKhi Flow l\u1ed7i, t\xf4i d\xf9ng c\xe1ch n\xe0y:\\n\\n1. **Enable Debug Mode** trong Flow Builder\\n2. **Add Debug Elements** \u0111\u1ec3 log gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb\\n3. **Run Test** v\u1edbi sample data\\n4. **Review Debug Logs** trong Setup > Debug Logs\\n\\n```yaml\\nDebug Steps:\\n1. Open Flow Builder\\n2. Click Debug menu\\n3. Enable Debug Mode\\n4. Add text template: \\"Task Name: {!Task.Name}\\"\\n5. Run Flow with sample record\\n6. Check Debug Logs for values\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Nh\u1eefng l\u1ed7i t\xf4i g\u1eb7p ph\u1ea3i\\n\\n### L\u1ed7i 1: Roll-up Summary kh\xf4ng ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng\\n\\n**V\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1**: T\xf4i t\u1ea1o Roll-up Summary tr\xean Project nh\u01b0ng kh\xf4ng th\u1ea5y gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb.\\n\\n**Nguy\xean nh\xe2n**: Qu\xean set relationship l\xe0 Master-Detail.\\n\\n**Gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p**: Chuy\u1ec3n t\u1eeb Lookup sang Master-Detail relationship.\\n\\n### L\u1ed7i 2: Flow qu\xe1 nhi\u1ec1u records\\n\\n**V\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1**: Task Due Date Reminder Flow g\u1eedi h\xe0ng tr\u0103m email tr\xf9ng l\u1eb7p.\\n\\n**Nguy\xean nh\xe2n**: Kh\xf4ng c\xf3 check condition \u0111\u1ec3 tr\xe1nh g\u1eedi l\u1eb7p.\\n\\n**Gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p**: Th\xeam field `Reminder_Sent__c` v\xe0 check tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi g\u1eedi.\\n\\n### L\u1ed7i 3: Validation qu\xe1 nghi\xeam ng\u1eb7t\\n\\n**V\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1**: Kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 update Task sau khi t\u1ea1o.\\n\\n**Nguy\xean nh\xe2n**: Validation Rule qu\xe1 broad.\\n\\n**Gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p**: Th\xeam exception cho Admin users v\xe0 System profile.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Best Practices \xe1p d\u1ee5ng\\n\\n### 1. Naming Convention\\n\\n```\\nCustom Objects: PascalCase + __c\\n  - Project__c, Task__c, Milestone__c\\n\\nCustom Fields: PascalCase + __c\\n  - Start_Date__c, Status__c, Priority__c\\n\\nFormula Fields: Descriptive names\\n  - Days_Remaining__c, Project_Health__c\\n\\nFlows: Descriptive + Type\\n  - NewProject_Notification\\n  - TaskDueDate_Reminder\\n  - Milestone_UpdateProgress\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Documentation\\n\\nT\u1ea1o README cho m\u1ed7i Flow:\\n\\n```markdown\\n# New Project Notification Flow\\n\\n## Purpose\\nG\u1eedi email cho team khi Project m\u1edbi \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o\\n\\n## Type\\nRecord-Triggered Flow (After Create)\\n\\n## Trigger Object\\nProject__c\\n\\n## Business Logic\\n1. Get Team Members from Project__c.Team__c\\n2. Send email notification\\n3. Log notification in Notification_Log__c\\n\\n## Last Updated\\n2026-01-26\\n\\n## Last Modified By\\n[Your Name]\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Testing Strategy\\n\\n```yaml\\nTest Scenarios:\\n1. Create Project \u2192 Verify email sent\\n2. Update Task due date \u2192 Verify reminder sent\\n3. Complete Milestone \u2192 Verify progress updated\\n4. Delete Project \u2192 Verify cascade delete\\n5. Security test \u2192 Verify users only see their data\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc8 K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c\\n\\nSau 1 tu\u1ea7n x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng:\\n\\n- \u2705 **3 Custom Objects** v\u1edbi \u0111\xfang relationships\\n- \u2705 **20+ Custom Fields** (various types)\\n- \u2705 **7 Flow automations** ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng t\u1ed1t\\n- \u2705 **3 Reports** v\xe0 **1 Dashboard**\\n- \u2705 **Security model** \u0111\xfang chu\u1ea9n\\n- \u2705 **100% test coverage** cho t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 scenarios\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c\\n\\n1. **Planning is everything**: \u0110\u1eebng b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u code tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi c\xf3 thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf r\xf5 r\xe0ng.\\n2. **Test early, test often**: \u0110\u1eebng ch\u1edd \u0111\u1ebfn khi ho\xe0n th\xe0nh m\u1edbi test.\\n3. **Document everything**: B\u1ea1n s\u1ebd qu\xean n\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng ghi l\u1ea1i.\\n4. **Start simple**: T\u1ea1o MVP tr\u01b0\u1edbc, sau \u0111\xf3 improve.\\n5. **Learn from mistakes**: M\u1ed7i l\u1ed7i l\xe0 m\u1ed9t b\xe0i h\u1ecdc.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcad L\u1eddi khuy\xean cho b\u1ea1n\\n\\nN\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n \u0111ang x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng app c\u1ee7a ri\xeang m\xecnh:\\n\\n1. **\u0110\u1eebng b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u v\u1edbi m\u1ed9t app qu\xe1 l\u1edbn**: B\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u v\u1edbi MVP.\\n2. **S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Flow thay v\xec code khi c\xf3 th\u1ec3**: N\xf3 d\u1ec5 maintain h\u01a1n.\\n3. **Test security**: \u0110\u1eebng qu\xean test v\u1edbi user profiles kh\xe1c nhau.\\n4. **Backup your work**: Export metadata th\u01b0\u1eddng xuy\xean.\\n5. **Ask for feedback**: Nh\u1eadn feedback s\u1edbm v\xe0 th\u01b0\u1eddng xuy\xean.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**B\xe0i vi\u1ebft ti\u1ebfp theo**: [T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng h\xf3a v\u1edbi Flow: Nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u t\xf4i \u01b0\u1edbc m\xecnh bi\u1ebft s\u1edbm h\u01a1n](#) (coming soon)\\n\\nB\u1ea1n c\xf3 kinh nghi\u1ec7m g\xec v\u1ec1 x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng custom app? Chia s\u1ebb b\xean d\u01b0\u1edbi nh\xe9! \ud83d\udcac\\n\\n**Tags**: #Salesforce #PlatformDeveloperI #Admin #Flow #ProjectApp #BestPractices"},{"id":"hanh-trinh-tuan-1-admin-flow","metadata":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/hanh-trinh-tuan-1-admin-flow","editUrl":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce/tree/main/website/blog/blog/2026-01-25-hanh-trinh-tuan-1-admin-flow.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-25-hanh-trinh-tuan-1-admin-flow.md","title":"H\xe0nh tr\xecnh Tu\u1ea7n 1: L\xe0m ch\u1ee7 Qu\u1ea3n tr\u1ecb Salesforce","description":"H\xf4m nay t\xf4i b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u h\xe0nh tr\xecnh 4 tu\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ec3 v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I. Tu\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean t\u1eadp trung v\xe0o Qu\u1ea3n tr\u1ecb Salesforce v\xe0 Flow Automation. \u0110\xe2y l\xe0 nh\u1eefng ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng c\u1ef1c k\u1ef3 quan tr\u1ecdng.","date":"2026-01-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"tuan-1","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/tuan-1"},{"inline":true,"label":"admin","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/admin"},{"inline":true,"label":"flow","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/flow"},{"inline":true,"label":"quan-tri","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/quan-tri"},{"inline":true,"label":"bat-dau","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/tags/bat-dau"}],"readingTime":4.07,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"H\u1ecdc L\u1ea1i","title":"Salesforce Platform Developer I Learner","url":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497/learn-salesforce","page":{"permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/authors/hoclai"},"description":"Chia s\u1ebb h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 kinh nghi\u1ec7m v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 Salesforce Platform Developer I trong 4 tu\u1ea7n","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/lehoaibao130497.png","key":"hoclai"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hanh-trinh-tuan-1-admin-flow","title":"H\xe0nh tr\xecnh Tu\u1ea7n 1: L\xe0m ch\u1ee7 Qu\u1ea3n tr\u1ecb Salesforce","authors":["hoclai"],"tags":["tuan-1","admin","flow","quan-tri","bat-dau"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng \u1ee8ng d\u1ee5ng Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd D\u1ef1 \xe1n: M\u1eb9o v\xe0 Th\u1ee7 thu\u1eadt","permalink":"/learn-salesforce/blog/xay-dung-project-management-app"}},"content":"H\xf4m nay t\xf4i b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u h\xe0nh tr\xecnh 4 tu\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ec3 v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua k\u1ef3 thi ch\u1ee9ng ch\u1ec9 **Salesforce Platform Developer I**. Tu\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean t\u1eadp trung v\xe0o **Qu\u1ea3n tr\u1ecb Salesforce** v\xe0 **Flow Automation**. \u0110\xe2y l\xe0 nh\u1eefng ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng c\u1ef1c k\u1ef3 quan tr\u1ecdng.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf M\u1ee5c ti\xeau Tu\u1ea7n 1\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean mang l\u1ea1i nh\u1eefng n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng v\u1eefng ch\u1eafc v\u1ec1:\\n\\n- **Salesforce Administration**: Hi\u1ec3u v\u1ec1 Objects, Fields, Relationships\\n- **Security**: Sharing rules, Profile, Permission Sets\\n- **Flow Automation**: X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng c\xe1c quy tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng h\xf3a m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n code\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcda Nh\u1eefng g\xec t\xf4i h\u1ecdc \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c\\n\\n### 1. Custom Objects & Fields\\n\\nT\xf4i \u0111\xe3 h\u1ecdc c\xe1ch t\u1ea1o Custom Objects v\xe0 hi\u1ec3u c\xe1c lo\u1ea1i fields kh\xe1c nhau:\\n\\n- **Text Fields**: D\xf9ng cho th\xf4ng tin v\u0103n b\u1ea3n ng\u1eafn\\n- **Number Fields**: D\xf9ng cho s\u1ed1 li\u1ec7u c\u1ea7n t\xednh to\xe1n\\n- **Picklist Fields**: Cung c\u1ea5p c\xe1c l\u1ef1a ch\u1ecdn c\xf3 s\u1eb5n\\n- **Formula Fields**: T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng t\xednh to\xe1n gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb d\u1ef1a tr\xean c\xe1c fields kh\xe1c\\n- **Lookup & Master-Detail Relationships**: Thi\u1ebft l\u1eadp quan h\u1ec7 gi\u1eefa objects\\n\\n**L\u1eddi khuy\xean**: Lu\xf4n suy ngh\u0129 v\u1ec1 m\xf4 h\xecnh d\u1eef li\u1ec7u tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u t\u1ea1o. T\u1ea1o m\u1ed9t diagram gi\xfap b\u1ea1n h\xecnh dung r\xf5 h\u01a1n v\u1ec1 c\xe1c quan h\u1ec7.\\n\\n### 2. Security Model\\n\\nSalesforce c\xf3 m\u1ed9t m\xf4 h\xecnh b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt kh\xe1 ph\u1ee9c t\u1ea1p nh\u01b0ng m\u1ea1nh m\u1ebd:\\n\\n- **Profiles**: X\xe1c \u0111\u1ecbnh nh\u1eefng g\xec ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m (Object-level security)\\n- **Permission Sets**: Cung c\u1ea5p quy\u1ec1n truy c\u1eadp b\u1ed5 sung m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n thay \u0111\u1ed5i Profile\\n- **Role Hierarchy**: X\xe1c \u0111\u1ecbnh quy\u1ec1n truy c\u1eadp d\u1eef li\u1ec7u (Record-level security)\\n- **Sharing Rules**: M\u1edf r\u1ed9ng quy\u1ec1n truy c\u1eadp cho c\xe1c nh\xf3m ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3\\n\\n**B\xe0i h\u1ecdc quan tr\u1ecdng**: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Permission Sets thay v\xec t\u1ea1o qu\xe1 nhi\u1ec1u Profiles. N\xf3 gi\xfap qu\u1ea3n l\xfd d\u1ec5 d\xe0ng h\u01a1n.\\n\\n### 3. Flow Builder\\n\\nFlow l\xe0 c\xf4ng c\u1ee5 m\u1ea1nh m\u1ebd nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng h\xf3a m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n code. T\xf4i \u0111\xe3 h\u1ecdc:\\n\\n- **Screen Flows**: T\u1ea1o c\xe1c quy tr\xecnh c\xf3 giao di\u1ec7n ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng\\n- **Record-Triggered Flows**: T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\u1ea1y khi record \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o, c\u1eadp nh\u1eadt ho\u1eb7c x\xf3a\\n- **Scheduled Flows**: Ch\u1ea1y t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng theo l\u1ecbch tr\xecnh\\n- **Auto-Launched Flows**: Ch\u1ea1y ng\u1ea7m m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n giao di\u1ec7n ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng\\n\\n**V\xed d\u1ee5 th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf**: T\xf4i \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o m\u1ed9t Flow t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng g\u1eedi email th\xf4ng b\xe1o khi m\u1ed9t task \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ho\xe0n th\xe0nh.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udca1 Nh\u1eefng th\xe1ch th\u1ee9c v\xe0 c\xe1ch v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua\\n\\n### Th\xe1ch th\u1ee9c 1: Hi\u1ec3u Security Model\\nL\xfac \u0111\u1ea7u, t\xf4i r\u1ea5t b\u1ed1i r\u1ed1i v\u1edbi s\u1ef1 kh\xe1c bi\u1ec7t gi\u1eefa Profile v\xe0 Permission Sets.\\n\\n**Gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p**: T\xf4i \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o m\u1ed9t b\u1ea3ng so s\xe1nh v\xe0 th\u1eed nghi\u1ec7m t\u1eebng lo\u1ea1i trong Developer Org. Th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf gi\xfap t\xf4i hi\u1ec3u nhanh h\u01a1n nhi\u1ec1u.\\n\\n### Th\xe1ch th\u1ee9c 2: Debug Flow\\nKhi Flow kh\xf4ng ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng nh\u01b0 mong \u0111\u1ee3i, t\xf4i kh\xf4ng bi\u1ebft c\xe1ch t\xecm l\u1ed7i.\\n\\n**Gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p**: S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng **Flow Debugger** trong Setup. N\xf3 cho ph\xe9p ch\u1ea1y Flow t\u1eebng b\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0 xem gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb c\u1ee7a t\u1eebng bi\u1ebfn.\\n\\n### Th\xe1ch th\u1ee9c 3: Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd th\u1eddi gian\\nV\u1edbi nhi\u1ec1u Trailhead modules v\xe0 c\xe1c b\xe0i t\u1eadp, t\xf4i c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y qu\xe1 t\u1ea3i.\\n\\n**Gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p**: \\n- Chia nh\u1ecf tasks th\xe0nh c\xe1c m\u1ee5c h\xe0ng ng\xe0y\\n- D\xe0nh 4 gi\u1edd bu\u1ed5i s\xe1ng cho Trailhead\\n- 5 gi\u1edd bu\u1ed5i chi\u1ec1u cho th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh\\n- 2 gi\u1edd bu\u1ed5i t\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ec3 review v\xe0 chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho ng\xe0y mai\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf89 K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 Tu\u1ea7n 1\\n\\nCu\u1ed1i tu\u1ea7n 1, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh:\\n\\n- \u2705 **12 Trailhead badges** v\u1ec1 Admin & Flow\\n- \u2705 **Project Management App** ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh v\u1edbi:\\n  - Custom Objects: Project, Task, Milestone\\n  - Automation v\u1edbi Flow\\n  - Security settings \u0111\xfang chu\u1ea9n\\n- \u2705 **7 Flow automations** kh\xe1c nhau\\n- \u2705 **Hi\u1ec3u r\xf5** m\xf4 h\xecnh b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt Salesforce\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcad Nh\u1eefng b\xe0i h\u1ecdc quan tr\u1ecdng\\n\\n1. **Th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh l\xe0 ch\xeca kh\xf3a**: \u0110\u1eebng ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u1ecdc t\xe0i li\u1ec7u, h\xe3y l\xe0m theo ngay l\u1eadp t\u1ee9c.\\n2. **\u0110\u1eebng s\u1ee3 sai**: Developer Edition l\xe0 \u0111\u1ec3 th\u1eed nghi\u1ec7m. T\u1ea1o, x\xf3a, t\u1ea1o l\u1ea1i - \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 c\xe1ch t\u1ed1t nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec3 h\u1ecdc.\\n3. **Ghi ch\xfa m\u1ecdi th\u1ee9**: T\xf4i \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o m\u1ed9t repository ri\xeang \u0111\u1ec3 l\u01b0u l\u1ea1i nh\u1eefng g\xec m\xecnh h\u1ecdc.\\n4. **H\u1ecfi khi g\u1eb7p kh\xf3**: Salesforce Stack Exchange l\xe0 n\u01a1i tuy\u1ec7t v\u1eddi \u0111\u1ec3 t\xecm c\xe2u tr\u1ea3 l\u1eddi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb cho Tu\u1ea7n 2\\n\\nTu\u1ea7n 2 s\u1ebd t\u1eadp trung v\xe0o **Apex** v\xe0 **SOQL** - l\u1eadp tr\xecnh backend. T\xf4i r\u1ea5t h\xe0o h\u1ee9ng v\xec \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 ph\u1ea7n th\xfa v\u1ecb nh\u1ea5t!\\n\\n**K\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch Tu\u1ea7n 2**:\\n- T\xecm hi\u1ec3u Apex syntax v\xe0 structure\\n- Vi\u1ebft Apex Triggers\\n- Th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh SOQL queries\\n- T\u1ea1o Test Classes\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcdd L\u1eddi khuy\xean cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u\\n\\nN\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u h\xe0nh tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc Salesforce, \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 l\u1eddi khuy\xean c\u1ee7a t\xf4i:\\n\\n1. **\u0110\u1eebng v\u1ed9i v\xe3**: H\xe3y d\xe0nh th\u1eddi gian hi\u1ec3u r\xf5 nh\u1eefng ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n.\\n2. **T\u1ea1o Developer Org ngay**: Th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh tr\xean ch\xednh org c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n.\\n3. **L\xe0m theo Trailhead**: N\xf3 cung c\u1ea5p l\u1ed9 tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp tuy\u1ec7t v\u1eddi.\\n4. **Tham gia c\u1ed9ng \u0111\u1ed3ng**: Salesforce Developer Community r\u1ea5t h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3.\\n5. **Ki\xean nh\u1eabn**: Ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c s\u1ebd t\xedch l\u0169y theo th\u1eddi gian, \u0111\u1eebng n\u1ea3n l\xf2ng.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Ti\u1ebfp theo**: [X\xe2y d\u1ef1ng \u1ee8ng d\u1ee5ng Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd D\u1ef1 \xe1n: M\u1eb9o v\xe0 Th\u1ee7 thu\u1eadt](#) (coming soon)\\n\\nB\u1ea1n c\xf3 c\xe2u h\u1ecfi g\xec v\u1ec1 Tu\u1ea7n 1? H\xe3y \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea1i b\xecnh lu\u1eadn b\xean d\u01b0\u1edbi nh\xe9! \ud83d\udcac\\n\\n**Tags**: #Salesforce #PlatformDeveloperI #Admin #Flow #LearningJourney"}]}}')}}]);